Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.32,0:00:12.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Set, hut!\N{\rCHT}開始{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.57,0:00:21.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Nice job, nice job. Tempo, tempo. Let's go.\N{\rCHT}很好 很好 速度 速度 上{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.08,0:00:25.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Reset.\N{\rCHT}重來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.16,0:00:26.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tempo, tempo. Let's pick it up this time, boys.\N{\rCHT}速度 速度 繼續戰鬥 孩子們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.08,0:00:29.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,What personnel they got, Coach? All right, let's change it.\N{\rCHT}教練 他們什麼陣容？好的 我們換{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.24,0:00:31.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wall right, wall right.\N{\rCHT}右側 右側{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.12,0:00:34.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Make sure you pick off the flyer. Here we go, here we go. Everybody up!\N{\rCHT}確保接住球 上 上 動起來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.12,0:00:36.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ready. Set!\N{\rCHT}準備 預備{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.24,0:00:41.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Set, hut!\N{\rCHT}預備 開始{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.72,0:00:48.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,There you go. Nice job. Nice job.\N{\rCHT}這邊 不錯 不錯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.08,0:00:58.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mike did. Someone to help me with maximum protection. Mike did.\N{\rCHT}邁克拼盡全力保護我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.04,0:01:00.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Someone to help me call the play. Mike did.\N{\rCHT}邁克幫我訓練{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.80,0:01:03.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Someone to help me get the team in line. Mike did it.\N{\rCHT}邁克幫我融入全隊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.56,0:01:05.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mike controlled it, Mike ran it.\N{\rCHT}邁克掌控全域 邁克一直在做{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.85,0:01:07.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,We needed him, we used him,\N{\rCHT}我們需要他 不能沒有他{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.82,0:01:09.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,we leaned on him.\N{\rCHT}他是我們的依靠{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.82,0:01:13.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,He was our strength in our offense.\N{\rCHT}他是我們力量的源泉{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.20,0:01:16.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,I know this man. I know his backside as well as anybody.\N{\rCHT}我知道他 我比所有人都瞭解他{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.03,0:01:23.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Simply, nothing has ever compared to Mike Webster.\N{\rCHT}坦白講 再好的形容詞用在邁克·韋伯斯特身上都不為過{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.75,0:01:29.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, the greatest center in the history of the National Football League,\N{\rCHT}女士們先生們 將進入美國職業橄欖球聯盟名人堂歷史的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.93,0:01:33.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,your inductee into the Hall of Fame, number 52, "Iron Mike" Webster!\N{\rCHT}他身穿52號球衣"鐵人"邁克·韋伯斯特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.64,0:01:37.67,CHT,,0,0,0,,{\c&He0e0e0&\fs40}震盪效應
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.44,0:01:47.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'd like to begin obviously,\N{\rCHT}顯然 我喜歡這個開局{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.96,0:01:51.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,I want it to be fun, but I want to be truthful.\N{\rCHT}我想試著幽默一點 但我更想真實點{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.21,0:01:58.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because the people out there are tremendous fans.\N{\rCHT}畢竟這兒還是有大量的球迷{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.79,0:02:02.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Locally, but as we go through this,\N{\rCHT}但是當我們站在現場感受這一切{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.64,0:02:07.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,I want you to understand the greatest thing that has happened to me,\N{\rCHT}我希望你們能明白 對於我來說最棒的事情{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.90,0:02:11.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,in my experience in professional football,\N{\rCHT}是在我的橄欖球職業生涯裡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.09,0:02:18.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,is to have the opportunity to work with people with a common goal.\N{\rCHT}是能夠有機會和有共同目標的人一起工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.45,0:02:23.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,And with the same purpose, and to sacrifice...\N{\rCHT}為了同樣的目標 不惜一切…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.59,0:02:38.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you this, it's painful to play football, obviously.\N{\rCHT}我想說 打橄欖球顯然是不容易的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.06,0:02:43.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,And it's not a lot of fun out there, to be in two-a-day drills\N{\rCHT}訓練並沒有什麼樂趣 夏天度日如年地操練{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.91,0:02:50.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,in the heat of summer, banging heads,it's not a natural thing.\N{\rCHT}頭頂著頭 這不正常{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.12,0:03:07.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,I was scared to fail, honest to god, I was scared I'd fail.\N{\rCHT}我害怕失敗 真的 我很害怕{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.47,0:03:10.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm still scared of that.\N{\rCHT}到現在我都很怕{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.81,0:03:45.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,And all we have to do is finish the game.\N{\rCHT}而我們要做的就是結束比賽{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.26,0:03:50.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,If we finish, we win. Yeah\N{\rCHT}當比賽結束 我們贏了 就是這樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.77,0:04:05.62,CHT,,0,0,0,,{\c&He0e0e0&\fs26}基於真實故事
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.43,0:04:11.72,CHT,,0,0,0,,{\c&He0e0e0&\fs20}賓夕法尼亞州  匹茲堡
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.19,0:04:16.88,CHT,,0,0,0,,{\c&He0e0e0&\fs30}2002年 九月
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.47,0:04:23.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,The State has asked,\N{\rCHT}聯邦發問{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.07,0:04:26.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,after a lengthy trial, a death sentence,\N{\rCHT}經過漫長的審議 一次死刑判決{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.60,0:04:30.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,and two appeals, why we would learn anything new from you?\N{\rCHT}兩次上訴 我們為什麼要相信你會帶來新證據？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.74,0:04:33.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dr.Omalu, Do you have a medical degree?\N{\rCHT}奧奧馬魯醫生 你有醫學學位嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.30,0:04:38.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, from the University of Nigeria.\N{\rCHT}是的 奈及利亞大學的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.78,0:04:41.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,At Enugu, Nigeria.\N{\rCHT}在埃努古 奈及利亞{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.48,0:04:49.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,I did my residency at Columbia University Medical School in New York.\N{\rCHT}我居住在紐約的哥倫比亞大學醫學院{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.14,0:04:55.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,I also have masters degrees in public health and epidemiology.\N{\rCHT}我還有公共衛生和流行病的碩士學位{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.55,0:05:00.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,In addition, I am a certified physician executive,\N{\rCHT}同時 我還是個有執照的醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.39,0:05:04.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,with a specialty in emergency medicine.\N{\rCHT}專長是急診醫學{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.21,0:05:07.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,And of course I'm board certified in\N{\rCHT}當然 委員會認證了我的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.02,0:05:11.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,forensic pathology, clinical pathology and anatomic pathology.\N{\rCHT}法醫病理學 臨床病理學 還有解剖病理學{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.67,0:05:17.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,My focus is neuropathology, the examination of the brain.\N{\rCHT}我的中心工作是神經病理學 對大腦的研究{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.16,0:05:19.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,- While working as a... - I'm sorry, so sorry, I'm sorry.\N{\rCHT}- 當開始研究… - 抱歉 抱歉{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.73,0:05:23.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am also completing my MBA\N{\rCHT}我還在卡耐基馬林大學{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.12,0:05:25.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,at Carnegie Malin University.\N{\rCHT}完成了我的工商管理碩士學業{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.43,0:05:30.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, uh, and before I came to America, a Masters Degree\N{\rCHT}在我來美國之前 我還有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.76,0:05:34.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,in the Theory of Music from the Royal School of Music in London.\N{\rCHT}倫敦皇家音樂學院音樂理論的碩士學位{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.50,0:05:42.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,But, oh, your original question, what I can add?\N{\rCHT}不過 你先問了 我還要補充什麼嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.18,0:05:50.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,My specialty is the science of death.\N{\rCHT}我的專業是死因調查{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.25,0:05:55.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,I think more about why people die than I do the way people live.\N{\rCHT}比起生活的意義 我更關注死亡的原因{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.89,0:06:01.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hands of the deceased.\N{\rCHT}死者的手{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.37,0:06:04.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Broken and dislodged fingernails.\N{\rCHT}破碎和脫落的指甲{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.16,0:06:08.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,The hands of a woman, who fought wildly, for her life.\N{\rCHT}一個 曾為自己的生命 激烈反抗過的女人的手{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.71,0:06:10.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,And lost...\N{\rCHT}最終失去了…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.65,0:06:13.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,The hands of the defendant, Thomas Chambers,\N{\rCHT}被告湯瑪斯·錢伯斯的手{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.96,0:06:17.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,and that is in fact the blood of the victim.\N{\rCHT}這實際上是受害者的血{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.04,0:06:19.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then doesn't that suggest that the state has the right man?\N{\rCHT}這不就證明政府抓對認了嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.65,0:06:21.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,I thought so, until I heard\N{\rCHT}我原以為是這樣 直到我聽到{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.90,0:06:26.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hour 217 of Mr Chamber's police interview.\N{\rCHT}員警對錢伯斯先生217小時的調查內容{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.11,0:06:29.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,I heard him very clearly say: "I hate blood".\N{\rCHT}我很清楚地聽見他說:"我討厭血"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.44,0:06:33.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,I had a tooth pulled as a child once,\N{\rCHT}小時候我拔過一次牙{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.44,0:06:35.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,and it would not stop bleeding.\N{\rCHT}牙齦不停地出血{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.73,0:06:37.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,- So I got curious. - what about?\N{\rCHT}- 這樣我就覺得奇怪了 - 怎麼了？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.78,0:06:40.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hands, I could not reconcile...\N{\rCHT}那些手 我不能理解…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.47,0:06:45.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,these conflicting sets of hands. So my mind is going mad...\N{\rCHT}衝突的雙手 我覺得我快要瘋了…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.15,0:06:46.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,So I'm trying to figure out...\N{\rCHT}所以我想弄清楚…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.04,0:06:49.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,If Thomas Chambers' family has a history of hemophilia.\N{\rCHT}湯瑪斯·錢伯斯家族是不是有血友病的歷史{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.84,0:06:52.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,So I asked his father and his father said no.\N{\rCHT}所以我去問他的父親 但是他的父親說沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.84,0:06:56.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,But, there is a strain of hemophilia, hemophilia A...\N{\rCHT}但是 有一種血友病 A型血友病…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.78,0:06:58.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,It is so rare that it is never tested for...\N{\rCHT}它太罕見了所以從沒去檢測…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.88,0:07:02.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mr. Chambers tested positive for hemophilia A...\N{\rCHT}錢伯斯先生的A型血友病檢測結果是陽性…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.96,0:07:08.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,His hands may have touched the victim perhaps, to aid her as he claims,\N{\rCHT}他的手可能接觸過受害者 如他所說是要幫她{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.26,0:07:10.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,If his hands had been the murder weapon,\N{\rCHT}如果他用手去殺人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.48,0:07:12.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,if he had been scratched or bitten,\N{\rCHT}如果他被抓了或咬到了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.10,0:07:15.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,he would have bled to death.\N{\rCHT}他會流血而死{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.23,0:07:19.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,If the state of Pennsylvania, moves forward to execute,\N{\rCHT}如果賓夕法尼亞州法院執行了死刑判決{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.05,0:07:22.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,You would be killing an innocent man.\N{\rCHT}你們將會殺死一個無辜的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.98,0:08:32.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Happy Birthday to... - Way to go Joe.\N{\rCHT}- 生日快樂… - 喬 走開{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.67,0:08:38.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Good morning, Gracie. - Good morning, Dr.Omalu.\N{\rCHT}- 早上好 翠西 - 早上好 奧奧馬魯醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.10,0:08:40.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Here are the cases for today. - This is from yesterday.\N{\rCHT}- 這是今天的記錄 - 這是昨天的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.56,0:08:43.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, I got a full room today, cycle them through.\N{\rCHT}嘿 整間房子都滿了 開始檢查吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.31,0:08:44.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes sir.\N{\rCHT}嗯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.12,0:08:53.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's begin with Rachel Greene.\N{\rCHT}從瑞秋·格林開始吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.30,0:09:21.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay Rachel, I need your help.\N{\rCHT}瑞秋 我需要你的説明{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.19,0:09:24.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,We are in this together.\N{\rCHT}現在我們是一起的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.84,0:09:26.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Please help me to find out what happened to you.\N{\rCHT}請幫我找出發生在你身上的事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.80,0:09:29.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Here we go... - Danny, come on.\N{\rCHT}- 一起來吧… - 丹尼 拜託{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.43,0:09:35.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Gracie...\N{\rCHT}翠西…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.00,0:09:39.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dr.Omalu uses different stuff, makes less of a mess.\N{\rCHT}奧奧馬魯醫生使用不同的工具 減少交叉感染{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.63,0:10:32.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Possible cause of relationship between...\N{\rCHT}可能是它們之間的關係惡化了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.16,0:10:35.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,self-medication and early head trauma.\N{\rCHT}自行用藥和早期頭部創傷{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.38,0:10:37.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Leading to narcotics abuse and overdo\N{\rCHT}導致了藥物的濫用{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.02,0:10:40.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're not her shrink, Bennet.\N{\rCHT}你不是精神病學家 班尼特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.25,0:10:42.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,If I know how she lived, I know why she died.\N{\rCHT}如果我知道她的生活狀況 我就知道她的死因了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.52,0:10:45.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,And you should be careful, Danny.\N{\rCHT}你應該小心點的 丹尼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.68,0:10:48.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,One day I may be rushing through your autopsy.\N{\rCHT}說不定哪天我會解剖你的屍體{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.49,0:10:58.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dr.Wecht, Dr.Omalu is here to see you.\N{\rCHT}威切特醫生 奧奧馬魯醫生來見你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.50,0:11:01.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know the reason why you're not back in Nigeria, don't you?\N{\rCHT}你知道你不回尼日尼亞去的原因嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.71,0:11:04.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, because I remind you of you.\N{\rCHT}知道 因為我提醒過你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.71,0:11:07.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Only less handsome. Sit.\N{\rCHT}別耍帥了 坐吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.95,0:11:14.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What the hell is going on down there? - Nothing, I'm doing my work, I'm fine.\N{\rCHT}- 到底是怎麼回事？- 沒事 我在做我的工作 我很好啊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.59,0:11:19.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're not fine, Danny hates your guts, I've never seen anything like it.\N{\rCHT}騙誰呢 丹尼討厭你的衝動 我從來沒有見過他像這樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.86,0:11:21.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,I think you're working a little too slow.\N{\rCHT}我我覺得你工作有點慢了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.91,0:11:25.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm a doctor, the dead are my patients.\N{\rCHT}我是一個醫生 死者是我的病人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.31,0:11:26.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,I treat them with respect.\N{\rCHT}我尊重他們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.00,0:11:28.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,But do you have to talk to them?\N{\rCHT}這就是你和他們談話的原因嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.74,0:11:31.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you have to do that, talk to them in your head.\N{\rCHT}如果必須談話 心中默念就好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.57,0:11:35.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,And we discussed the knives, you're still throwing them away.\N{\rCHT}我們談談手術刀吧 你還在丟棄手術刀{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.26,0:11:38.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're a public agency in Pittsburgh, they're expensive.\N{\rCHT}我們是匹茲堡的公共醫院 手術刀很貴的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.76,0:11:39.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Reuse them.\N{\rCHT}要重複利用{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.90,0:11:42.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Would you want me, to cut open your mother\N{\rCHT}你同意我拿用在連環殺手身上的手術刀{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.70,0:11:45.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,with the same knife I used on a serial killer?\N{\rCHT}給你的母親開刀嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.94,0:11:52.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'd probably request it.\N{\rCHT}同意 我求你了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.49,0:11:58.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,You need a girlfriend,\N{\rCHT}你該找個對象了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.76,0:12:02.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,You need to touch somebody alive once in a while occasionally.\N{\rCHT}你需要多和活人接觸{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.59,0:12:05.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,Living women, well occasionally they're a pain in the ass,\N{\rCHT}活的女人 雖然偶爾她們會很煩人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.63,0:12:07.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,but quite often they're amazing.\N{\rCHT}但更多的時候是比較有意思的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.20,0:12:08.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Give it a try.\N{\rCHT}試試吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.78,0:12:09.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}好吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.79,0:12:14.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just be, a little less of an artist, fit in a little more.\N{\rCHT}別那麼特立獨行 融入周圍{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.05,0:12:15.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes.\N{\rCHT}嗯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.44,0:12:18.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's another death row case, the guy's being railroaded.\N{\rCHT}這又是一個死刑案 這傢伙被陷害入獄了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.00,0:12:21.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,A thousand dollars for you.\N{\rCHT}這1000美元是你的了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.08,0:12:25.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cyril...\N{\rCHT}西瑞爾…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.23,0:13:00.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,Webby. Hey, man.\N{\rCHT}嗨 夥計{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.43,0:13:03.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am loving the digs.\N{\rCHT}我喜歡這住處{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.16,0:13:08.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mike? It's Justin.\N{\rCHT}邁克？我是賈斯汀{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.46,0:13:12.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,If I just sit with you a minute, huh?\N{\rCHT}我能和你一起坐一會兒嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.20,0:13:25.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,Joker.\N{\rCHT}你這傢伙{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.13,0:13:28.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're all worried about you, man.\N{\rCHT}我們都很擔心你 夥計{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.65,0:13:31.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you doing, Mike? Mike.\N{\rCHT}你要幹嘛？邁克 邁克{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.37,0:13:34.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Don't do it - It's alright...\N{\rCHT}- 別這樣 - 沒事的…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.28,0:13:39.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,I just, I don't wanna go to sleep.\N{\rCHT}我只是 我不想入睡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.20,0:13:44.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,I heard you sold your Super Bowl rings, Mike.\N{\rCHT}我聽說你把自己的超級碗戒指賣了 邁克{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.94,0:13:47.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your Super Bowl rings, Mike\N{\rCHT}超級碗的戒指啊 邁克{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.85,0:13:57.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mike, hey, Pam's your wife.\N{\rCHT}邁克 嘿 帕姆是你的妻子{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.04,0:14:01.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Garrett's your boy. - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 加勒特是你的兒子 - 嗯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.04,0:14:07.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm starting to forget things.\N{\rCHT}我開始忘記事情{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.71,0:14:12.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm saying this crazy crap to my kids.\N{\rCHT}我還對我的孩子們瘋言瘋語{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.15,0:14:14.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,I nearly pushed Keana into a wall.\N{\rCHT}我幾乎把基娜推到牆裡面{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.77,0:14:21.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I never thought I'd do that to her. - Well, don't... just don't give up.\N{\rCHT}- 我從沒想過我會那麼對她 - 不要… 不要放棄自己{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.66,0:14:24.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,All we gotta do...\N{\rCHT}我們所要做的…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.50,0:14:29.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,is finish the game. And we'll all be winners.\N{\rCHT}是結束比賽 那麼我們就是贏家{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.10,0:15:25.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Have a good day, it's good to see you\N{\rCHT}開心點 見到你很高興{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.56,0:15:28.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Oh, Bennet, a moment. - Yes, father?\N{\rCHT}- 班尼特 等一下 - 怎麼了 神父？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.82,0:15:33.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,- How are you. - We have a new member, a young lady from Kenya.\N{\rCHT}- 你好 - 我們有一個新朋友 一個來自肯亞的年輕女士{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.62,0:15:37.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,She came to us a couple of weeks ago and she needs our help.\N{\rCHT}她幾周前剛過來 她需要我們的説明{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.36,0:15:39.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sure, how much do you need, Father?\N{\rCHT}明白 你需要多少錢 神父？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.04,0:15:42.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,She needs shelter, Bennet, until we find her something permanent.\N{\rCHT}她需要住所 班尼特 直到她有工作穩定下來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.24,0:15:46.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Father, my... I... I'm working on my MBA, I'm studying... my books are all over everywhere.\N{\rCHT}神父 我… 我正在讀工商管理碩士 我忙著讀書 我的書扔的到處都是{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.68,0:15:48.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,She's a nice girl, she's from Nairobi.\N{\rCHT}她是個很不錯的女孩 從奈洛比過來的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.95,0:15:52.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Went to a British school, she wants to work.\N{\rCHT}在英國上的學 她想找個工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.15,0:15:54.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're letting her tidy around the church.\N{\rCHT}我們讓她打掃教堂{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.51,0:15:56.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,We're asking you because\N{\rCHT}我們請你幫忙 是因為{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.75,0:15:59.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,we know she'll be safe and cared for.\N{\rCHT}我們知道她會安全且被照顧地很好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.14,0:16:04.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I feel God in you, Bennet. - Thank you, father.\N{\rCHT}- 我知道你很善良 班尼特 - 謝謝 神父{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.08,0:16:07.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where is she?\N{\rCHT}她在哪？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.71,0:16:43.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,So... you can see.\N{\rCHT}呃… 如你所見{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.81,0:16:56.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,That is basically my office there.\N{\rCHT}這基本上是我的辦公室{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.35,0:17:05.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is that your father?\N{\rCHT}那是你父親嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.32,0:17:08.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ah yes, The Chief.\N{\rCHT}是的 還是個酋長{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.90,0:17:13.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Those are my peaches.\N{\rCHT}這是我的桃子{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.55,0:17:15.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,They should not be here.\N{\rCHT}不該在這的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.48,0:17:20.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your room, there is a...\N{\rCHT}你的房間 有…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.95,0:17:24.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,the key for you.\N{\rCHT}給你的鑰匙{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.87,0:17:33.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,How are you for money? I have something...\N{\rCHT}你有錢嗎？我有一些…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.20,0:17:41.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Need is not weak.\N{\rCHT}需求不代表軟弱{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.97,0:17:45.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Need is need.\N{\rCHT}需求就是需求{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.58,0:17:50.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,I know where you are, I was you.\N{\rCHT}我知道你的情況 我曾跟你一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.13,0:17:55.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,You are in America now, so,\N{\rCHT}你現在是在美國 所以{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.68,0:17:59.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,you have to be the best version of yourself.\N{\rCHT}你必須做最好的自己{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.11,0:18:05.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you don't know what that is, you pick something and fake it.\N{\rCHT}如果你不知道那是什麼 你就選一個並裝成那個樣子{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.50,0:18:09.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,I will put it there for you.\N{\rCHT}我替你把它放這兒{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.89,0:18:12.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What did you pick? - What did I pick?\N{\rCHT}- 你選的什麼？- 我選擇什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.62,0:18:18.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,- To fake. - I picked an older, bald headed white man.\N{\rCHT}- 偽裝 - 我選了一個又老又禿的白人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.89,0:18:22.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why an older, bald headed white man?\N{\rCHT}為什麼是個又老又禿的白人？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.77,0:18:27.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because he is the best at what he does.\N{\rCHT}因為他是他所從事的領域裡最傑出的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.42,0:18:31.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you want to see your room?\N{\rCHT}你想看看你的房間嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.76,0:18:48.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,I was a registered nurse.\N{\rCHT}我是一個有執照的護士{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.44,0:18:51.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,At the Aogakan hospital in Nairobi.\N{\rCHT}我曾在奈洛比的奧嘎刊醫院工作過{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.10,0:18:57.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,I understand, I meant no offense.\N{\rCHT}明白 無意冒犯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.98,0:19:05.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey , wake up. Hey.\N{\rCHT}嘿 醒醒{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.14,0:19:08.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wake up, you.\N{\rCHT}醒醒 叫你呢{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.08,0:19:10.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come on now, this ain't no hotel, you can't sleep here.\N{\rCHT}快點 這可不是酒店 你不能在這兒睡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.76,0:19:12.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Put down your window, let's go.\N{\rCHT}車窗放下來 走開{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.68,0:19:23.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're Mike Webster, right? Iron Mike.\N{\rCHT}你是邁克·韋伯斯特？真的嗎？鐵人邁克{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.01,0:19:27.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I called for him, he's coming. - Okay, well, I don't see him.\N{\rCHT}- 我打電話給他了 他就來 - 好吧 我沒有看到他{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.41,0:19:32.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on, Claude.\N{\rCHT}哦 拜託 克勞德{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.03,0:19:35.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come on, come on.\N{\rCHT}拜託 拜託{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.55,0:19:53.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mike, he's here.\N{\rCHT}邁克 他在這兒{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.90,0:19:56.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hey, Mike. - Look you, uh...\N{\rCHT}- 嗨 邁克 - 看看你…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.91,0:19:59.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Mike, can you hear me? - Oh, yeah, yeah. I just uh...\N{\rCHT}- 邁克 你能聽到我說話嗎？- 能 我只是…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.97,0:20:04.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,You just, uh, you just have to tell me to do, because I am...\N{\rCHT}你只要 呃 你只需要告訴我該怎麼做 因為我…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.48,0:20:06.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am freaking overwhelmed.\N{\rCHT}我不知道該幹嘛{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.26,0:20:08.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,- We're gonna get you some help, Mike. - What are you taking right now?\N{\rCHT}- 我們會給你一些幫助邁克 - 你現在在做什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.80,0:20:14.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,- The Ritalin. - Dexedrine, Prozac still takin all of those?\N{\rCHT}- 利他林 - 中樞神經刺激劑 百憂解 扭角羚都要嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.05,0:20:17.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Sit down. - Yeah, all of it, and super glue.\N{\rCHT}- 坐吧 - 是的 全部都要 還有強力膠{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.47,0:20:21.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Okay Mike - 3.5 Haldol, you call his wife,\N{\rCHT}- 好的邁克 - 3.5的氟呱啶醇 給他妻子打電話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.72,0:20:23.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,You tell her he is worse, he's a lot worse.\N{\rCHT}你告訴她 他現在很糟糕 非常糟糕{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.88,0:20:25.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,You were my doctor , You were my doctor, right?\N{\rCHT}你是我的醫生 你是我的醫生 對吧？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.72,0:20:29.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I was the team doctor I was everybody's... - Okay, the Team doctor.\N{\rCHT}- 我是隊醫 我是每個人的… - 好的 是隊醫{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.66,0:20:33.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay, alright then, the Team doctor. Then why aren't you helping me alright?\N{\rCHT}好吧好吧 隊醫 那你為什麼不把我治好啊？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.60,0:20:35.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I am going to help you... - You are not helping me...\N{\rCHT}- 我會幫助你的… - 你沒有…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.88,0:20:38.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You gotta fix this, you gotta fix this, alright? - Doctor?\N{\rCHT}- 你必須解決這裡的問題 你要解決這個問題 - 醫生嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.62,0:20:40.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,In here, Alright ?\N{\rCHT}這裡的問題 知道嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.30,0:20:43.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,And in here, I am dying in here.\N{\rCHT}還有這 非常難受{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.55,0:20:46.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I'm dying in here alright. - I'll take care of you, Mike.\N{\rCHT}- 難受死了 - 我會照顧你的 邁克{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.70,0:20:48.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's okay.\N{\rCHT}好了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.98,0:20:52.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let me give you something to help you rest, Mike.\N{\rCHT}讓我先幫助你休息一會 邁克{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.22,0:20:54.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,You want to rest, don't you?\N{\rCHT}你想要休息 是吧？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.46,0:20:58.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,I just want you to help me alright , I just want you to help me.\N{\rCHT}我只是想讓你幫幫我 我只是想讓你幫幫我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.90,0:21:02.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I'll help you, Mike. - Just help me.\N{\rCHT}- 我會幫你的 邁克 - 幫幫我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.80,0:21:06.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come and sit down.\N{\rCHT}過來坐下{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.60,0:21:13.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, go ahead, give me the drugs, give me the drugs\N{\rCHT}好吧 隨便了 打針吧 來點藥{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.92,0:21:17.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Show me how you're going to help me... - Don't move, Mike.\N{\rCHT}- 讓我看看你怎麼幫我… - 不要動 邁克{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.50,0:21:23.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come and sit down, Mike.\N{\rCHT}過來坐下 邁克{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.06,0:21:30.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come lay down, Mike.\N{\rCHT}來 躺下 邁克{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.53,0:21:37.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,You rest now. Mike.\N{\rCHT}現在開始休息 邁克{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.67,0:21:43.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What am I missing? - A tumor?\N{\rCHT}- 我漏掉了什麼嗎？- 腫瘤？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.97,0:21:47.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, all of his scans were clean.\N{\rCHT}不是 所有的掃描結果都是正常的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.35,0:22:28.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Over the years, the dauntless Webster had abandoned his family,\N{\rCHT}多年來 不屈不撓的韋伯斯特 已經放棄了他的家庭{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.32,0:22:31.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,slipped into financial chaos, and homelessness.\N{\rCHT}陷入經濟危機 無家可歸{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.36,0:22:33.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is a hard day for the city of Pittsburgh.\N{\rCHT}對匹茲堡來說這是艱難的一天{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.57,0:22:36.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,On a personal note, I can remember sitting down with my father,\N{\rCHT}在我的私人日記裡 我還記著 他和我父親坐在一起{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.65,0:22:39.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,and him giving me examples of hard work ethic.\N{\rCHT}並且他給我舉了工作模範的例子{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.44,0:22:42.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,And telling me when you get knocked down, you get back up again...\N{\rCHT}他告訴我 當你被撞倒了 你再爬起來…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.46,0:22:46.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I don't usually watch TV.\N{\rCHT}抱歉 我很少看電視{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.51,0:22:48.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then why do you have one?\N{\rCHT}那你為什麼有電視？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.60,0:22:51.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,One has a TV in this country.\N{\rCHT}這個國家每個人都有電視{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.53,0:23:04.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm Sorry, I don't usually eat breakfast.\N{\rCHT}哦 對不起 我通常不吃早餐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.80,0:23:07.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,One should eat breakfast in this country.\N{\rCHT}在這個國家每個人都應該吃早餐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.43,0:23:24.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dear God, thank you for the gifts. you have so graciously bestowed upon us.\N{\rCHT}親愛的上帝 謝謝您的饋贈 如此慷慨地給予我們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.14,0:23:28.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Please help us to continue to be deservant of your blessings.\N{\rCHT}請讓我們能一直得到您的庇佑和祝福{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.47,0:23:30.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Amen.\N{\rCHT}阿門{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.51,0:23:32.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bennet\N{\rCHT}班尼特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.57,0:23:35.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just hours after he was rushed to a nearby hospital,\N{\rCHT}在他被送往醫院的幾個小時後{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.35,0:23:37.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,Recall Hall of Famer, "Iron" Mike Webster...\N{\rCHT}撤銷名人堂成員"鐵人"邁克·韋伯斯特…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.97,0:23:39.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What is going on? - Mike Webster.\N{\rCHT}- 這到底是怎麼回事 - 邁克·韋伯斯特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.23,0:23:41.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who's Mike Webster?\N{\rCHT}誰是邁克·韋伯斯特？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.71,0:23:44.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's the greatest centre to ever play the game, he's a true warrior.\N{\rCHT}他是歷史上最偉大的中鋒 他是一個真正的勇士{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.76,0:23:49.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I'm sorry, what is a "centre"? - The big guy in the middle, hikes it.\N{\rCHT}- 對不起"中鋒"是什麼？- 中間的大個子{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.35,0:23:53.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,- My kid plays football because of this guy. - Okay. I'm sorry, I just did not know who he was.\N{\rCHT}- 我的孩子打橄欖球就是因為這傢伙 - 好吧 我很抱歉 我不知道他是誰{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.38,0:23:56.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're going to live in this town, you're going to work in this town, football is a good thing.\N{\rCHT}如果你要在這個城市生活 你要在這個城市工作 橄欖球是一個好東西{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.88,0:23:58.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,I freaking can't believe it's you.\N{\rCHT}我真不敢相信是你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.85,0:24:01.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look, as you know I was put on the schedule for this weekend.\N{\rCHT}你知道我這個週末的排程{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.60,0:24:03.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am put on the schedule for every weekend.\N{\rCHT}我每個週末都有安排{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.73,0:24:07.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come on, come on.\N{\rCHT}拜託 拜託{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.48,0:24:12.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,The whole town was out of work.\N{\rCHT}整個城市都停下來了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.79,0:24:15.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,He was the guy that gave us hope when there really was no hope.\N{\rCHT}在沒有希望的時候這個傢伙給了我們希望{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.28,0:24:19.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just... leave him be.\N{\rCHT}只是… 他離開了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.25,0:24:24.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look at his teeth.\N{\rCHT}看他的牙齒{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.33,0:24:28.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,He was pulling them out and supergluing them back in\N{\rCHT}他把它們拉出又用強力膠黏回去{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.39,0:24:32.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Gracie, full autopsy, please.\N{\rCHT}翠西 完整解剖{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.54,0:24:35.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, come on, man, there's no need to cut this man's body.\N{\rCHT}噢 拜託 夥計 沒必要切開他的身體吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.33,0:24:38.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why does an apparently healthy, favourite son of this city....\N{\rCHT}為什麼一個健康的 這個城市最受歡飲的人…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.88,0:24:43.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Become self mutilating and homeless at 50?\N{\rCHT}在50歲時開始虐待自己並且無家可歸？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.09,0:24:46.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cardiac arrest may be how he died but not why.\N{\rCHT}心臟停止跳動讓他死亡了 當那並不是死亡的原因{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.01,0:24:49.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Prepare the body, please.\N{\rCHT}清潔遺體{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.11,0:24:57.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,I think what he's saying is that...\N{\rCHT}我想他的意思是…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.53,0:25:01.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sometimes in life, you know you just...\N{\rCHT}有時候在生活中 你知道你…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.17,0:25:03.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're asked to leave it alone.\N{\rCHT}你想要隨它去吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.99,0:25:06.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,But sometimes you can't.\N{\rCHT}但是有時候你不能{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.69,0:25:11.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you think he believes it is a time I should leave it alone?\N{\rCHT}你覺得他認為這是個小事 我應該不管它嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.74,0:25:12.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, I don't.\N{\rCHT}不 沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.98,0:25:17.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,I never leave it alone, that's why people hate me.\N{\rCHT}我從不隨波逐流 那就是人們討厭我的原因{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.05,0:26:09.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mike... people are saying bad things about you.\N{\rCHT}邁克… 人們都在說你的壞話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.96,0:26:12.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,I can tell something is wrong.\N{\rCHT}我想說有些事情是錯的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.45,0:26:15.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,But I can't do this alone.\N{\rCHT}但是我自己一個人做不到{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.42,0:26:19.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,I need your help, to tell the world what happened to you.\N{\rCHT}我需要你的説明 告訴這個世界你身上發生了什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.89,0:27:29.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Uh, sorry...\N{\rCHT}哦 抱歉{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.52,0:27:36.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Regular folds of gray matter, no obvious contusions.\N{\rCHT}腦灰質褶皺正常 沒有明顯的挫傷{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.33,0:27:40.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,No shrinkage from Alzheimers.\N{\rCHT}沒有老年癡呆萎縮症狀{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.43,0:27:46.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?\N{\rCHT}怎麼了？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.81,0:27:52.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Can you show me the CT scan again please?\N{\rCHT}能把CT掃描件再給我看一下嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.60,0:28:00.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,- How old are these? - Six months.\N{\rCHT}- 這些東西多久了？- 六個月前的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.72,0:28:02.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Six months, okay.\N{\rCHT}六個月 行了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.54,0:28:21.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,His brain should be a mess, but...\N{\rCHT}他的大腦應該很糟糕 但是…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.09,0:28:25.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,It looks completely normal.\N{\rCHT}它看上去很正常{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.14,0:28:28.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Records say: severe headaches,\N{\rCHT}記錄中有:嚴重的頭痛{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.86,0:28:30.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,double vision, voices...\N{\rCHT}頭部會產生…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.44,0:28:33.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,in his head.\N{\rCHT}重影和重音{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.24,0:28:35.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,No documented concussions.\N{\rCHT}沒有腦震盪記錄{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.31,0:28:37.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,He did complain of dizziness.\N{\rCHT}他總是抱怨頭暈{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.61,0:28:40.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yes, How often? - Once.\N{\rCHT}- 噢 經常抱怨嗎？- 是的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.63,0:28:43.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,In 18 years of professional football?\N{\rCHT}18年的橄欖球職業生涯嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.27,0:28:45.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Joseph Maroon.\N{\rCHT}約瑟夫·馬路恩{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.91,0:28:49.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sign the certificate, sew him up.\N{\rCHT}在證明上簽字 縫合{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.08,0:28:53.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fix the brain, please.\N{\rCHT}固定大腦{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.80,0:28:57.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know we don't have the budget to do that.\N{\rCHT}你知道我們沒有那麼多的預算{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.41,0:29:00.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,People do not go mad for no reason, I'm going to continue looking.\N{\rCHT}人不會無緣無故發瘋 我要找到原因{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.68,0:29:05.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,- No, you're not going to. - Danny, you are out of line.\N{\rCHT}- 不可能 - 丹尼你過分了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.12,0:29:08.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hey, you do not speak to me like that. - I am the pathologist on duty.\N{\rCHT}- 嘿 不要這樣對我說話 - 我是值班的病理學家{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.89,0:29:13.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I am the pathologist on record. - Listen This is not your laboratory.\N{\rCHT}- 病理記錄上簽的我名字 - 聽好了 這不是你自己的實驗室{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.08,0:29:15.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,My hands are on this body If I am wrong, I am wrong.\N{\rCHT}我給這遺體做的檢查 如果我做錯了 那是我的錯誤{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.64,0:29:17.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,- And you are wrong - Not you, me\N{\rCHT}- 你就是錯了 - 不是你說了算 是我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.13,0:29:23.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Fix that brain. - Hey, I am going to make sure that they don't pay for any of this.\N{\rCHT}- 固定大腦 - 我要確保他們不為做這件事超支{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.22,0:29:26.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am going to write my orders for the tests that I need.\N{\rCHT}我會寫我要做的測試的清單{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.27,0:29:28.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Then you're paying for it yourself. - Yes, Danny.\N{\rCHT}- 那你自己付錢去 - 可以{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.69,0:29:31.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Please, exit my workplace.\N{\rCHT}請你離開我的工作室{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.44,0:29:36.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Please.\N{\rCHT}走開{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.80,0:29:40.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,In 25 years I've never requested a panel of tests like this.\N{\rCHT}25年來我從未如此要求過檢測小組{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.05,0:29:42.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you looking for?\N{\rCHT}你想要幹什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.38,0:29:47.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,There is not a single case, in a book or in life,\N{\rCHT}在書裡或者生活裡 從沒有發生過這樣的事情{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.41,0:29:51.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,where a man that healthy, went that mad, that young,\N{\rCHT}哪裡有一個健康年輕的男人像那樣瘋{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.90,0:29:55.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,with no visible abnormality of the brain.\N{\rCHT}而且大腦看起來很正常{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.45,0:30:00.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I don't know what I am looking for. - I can tell.\N{\rCHT}- 我不知道我在尋找什麼 - 我可以告訴你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.50,0:30:05.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,- It's going to cost you a fortune. - I understand.\N{\rCHT}- 它會花費你一大筆錢的 - 明白{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.96,0:30:12.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay, well, if you have to play hero, just make sure we both come out okay.\N{\rCHT}好吧 你要想成為英雄 但你得確保我們都不會有麻煩{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.02,0:30:55.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dr.Omalu, you got something today. I left it on your desk.\N{\rCHT}奧奧馬魯醫生 幫你收了一些東西 我放你桌子上了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.02,0:30:57.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N{\rCHT}謝謝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.58,0:31:24.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Prema...\N{\rCHT}普雷瑪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.54,0:31:28.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's very late. Where have you been?\N{\rCHT}這麼晚 你去哪了？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.61,0:31:34.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,I got a job.\N{\rCHT}我找到了一份工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.70,0:31:38.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Look at you... - Well, a shift.\N{\rCHT}- 你行的… - 嗯 一次轉變{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.54,0:31:42.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,At a home, feeding old people.\N{\rCHT}在別人家裡 照顧老年人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.43,0:31:45.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,That is fantastic, congratulations.\N{\rCHT}太好了 恭喜你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.39,0:31:48.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,What is that?\N{\rCHT}那是？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.09,0:31:51.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mike Webster.\N{\rCHT}邁克·韋伯斯特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.08,0:32:00.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Raise is worth a thousand dollars and here we go...\N{\rCHT}讓我們從現在開始去賺夠1000美元吧…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.86,0:32:07.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,Would you like me to get you a TV for your room?\N{\rCHT}要不要我買個電視放你臥室裡？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.59,0:32:12.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, this one will be fine.\N{\rCHT}不用了 一個就好了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.53,0:32:14.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\N{\rCHT}呃 好吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.07,0:32:28.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,I can't tell what you're more afraid of.\N{\rCHT}我不知道你在擔心什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.70,0:32:30.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,What you will find...\N{\rCHT}你會找到什麼…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.56,0:32:33.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,or what you won't\N{\rCHT}或者找不到什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.39,0:34:01.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, My God.\N{\rCHT}哦 我的天呐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.86,0:34:07.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, My God.\N{\rCHT}哦 天呐{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.56,0:34:37.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's get the Jacked Up No. 5\N{\rCHT}讓我們一起為5號加油{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.94,0:34:43.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bringing it again with the Rams vs Chargers, Mark Bulger gonna be delivering the ball to Tony Fisher.\N{\rCHT}公羊隊和閃電隊再次狹路相逢 馬克·布傑要傳球給托尼·費舍爾{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.63,0:34:45.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,throws it down around his feet,\N{\rCHT}球扔到他的腳下了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.31,0:34:48.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,So Donny Edwards is gonna level him right there.\N{\rCHT}丹尼·愛德華準備開始沖線了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.38,0:34:51.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Always be looking out for the big hit right there.\N{\rCHT}看來大個子總能在合適的時候發起衝擊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.23,0:34:53.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tony Fisher got Jacked Up.\N{\rCHT}托尼·費舍爾受傷了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.53,0:34:58.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,No.4, the Seahawks and the Chiefs, DJ Hackett.\N{\rCHT}4號 海鷹隊首領 DJ·哈科特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.70,0:35:03.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you gonna make the catch in time, lord gotta watch your back...\N{\rCHT}如果你想趕時間 請先看看你的身後…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.14,0:35:06.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Eyes on me, Eyes on me\N{\rCHT}看我 看著我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.62,0:35:07.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen...\N{\rCHT}先生們…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.20,0:35:12.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is a game of awareness. It is a game of desire.\N{\rCHT}這是需要思維遊戲 這是需要欲望的遊戲{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.08,0:35:14.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's why we have the three whistle drill.\N{\rCHT}這就是為什麼場上有三個裁判的原因{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.75,0:35:16.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's Go\N{\rCHT}動起來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.07,0:35:18.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,When I blow this whistle three times...\N{\rCHT}當你聽到三次哨聲…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.59,0:35:21.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,You seek out a team mate, any team mate\N{\rCHT}去尋找你的隊友 任何一個隊友{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.06,0:35:24.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,You make collision, You be physical, You be violent\N{\rCHT}像野獸一樣 去衝擊 去碰撞 暴力點{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.64,0:35:27.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bring it in here, let's go\N{\rCHT}就是現在 躁起來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.57,0:35:34.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,The only way you're going to get this players hands off of you, You grab him by his throat and you squeeze.\N{\rCHT}你想讓這個運動員放手的辦法只有一個 你要用盡全力去扼住他們的喉嚨{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.35,0:35:36.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,You choke him until shit runs down his leg.\N{\rCHT}緊緊扼住直到他大小便失禁{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.00,0:35:38.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you understand me?\N{\rCHT}聽明白了嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.91,0:35:55.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Drive, drive, get up.\N{\rCHT}沖 沖 沖起來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.00,0:35:58.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hit, drive, drive.\N{\rCHT}撞他 沖 沖{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.67,0:36:02.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jack wires in the Eagles, Dirk Johnson, and I'm gonna wait for this,\N{\rCHT}老鷹隊的傑克·維爾斯 德科·詹森 我一直在期待這一刻{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.36,0:36:05.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because the look on his face tells you that he got...\N{\rCHT}因為他臉上的表情在告訴你他…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.39,0:36:06.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Jacked up.\N{\rCHT}受傷了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.12,0:36:17.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,And our No.1 hit of the week Jon Kitna dropping back to pass\N{\rCHT}我們的1號幹翻了喬恩·科塔回到了替補區{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.26,0:36:22.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,and Shawn Spencer and lifts him off his feet.\N{\rCHT}肖恩·斯賓塞完成了對他的擒抱{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.34,0:36:26.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God. And Jon Kitna got: Jacked Up.\N{\rCHT}噢 天啊 喬恩·科塔傷了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.70,0:36:52.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,You should see this, Bennet.\N{\rCHT}你該看看這個 班尼特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.36,0:36:57.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's actually, really beautiful.\N{\rCHT}很好看 真的很精彩{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.36,0:37:01.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes he's got him touchdown.\N{\rCHT}他真的做到了 觸底得分{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.34,0:37:04.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,A tremendous catch.\N{\rCHT}一次關鍵的防守{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.16,0:37:09.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Can I show you something?\N{\rCHT}我能給你看一些東西嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.39,0:37:12.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,The human brain resides in a fluid...\N{\rCHT}這裡邊泡著人的腦體樣本…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.98,0:37:16.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,completely disconnected from the human brain.\N{\rCHT}完全脫離人的大腦{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.10,0:37:55.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bennet, will you relax? I can hear you breathing.\N{\rCHT}放鬆點 班尼特 我都能聽到你的呼吸聲{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.42,0:38:08.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is a really terrible brain.\N{\rCHT}這是一個有問題的大腦{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.06,0:38:14.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ever met the Great DeKosky before? Expect two minutes, tops.\N{\rCHT}之前從沒見過德庫思老師嗎？稍等兩分鐘{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.30,0:38:17.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is that him?\N{\rCHT}是他嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.87,0:38:20.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,So you're our prize graduate.\N{\rCHT}你就是那個優秀畢業生了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.13,0:38:41.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell him.\N{\rCHT}告訴他吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.75,0:38:47.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,- It's Mike Webster, the... - I know who Mike Webster is.\N{\rCHT}- 邁克·韋伯斯特 他是… - 我知道他是誰{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.09,0:38:50.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Steve, he was 50.\N{\rCHT}史蒂夫 他才五十歲{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.39,0:39:07.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,You have my attention.\N{\rCHT}你提起我的興致了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.38,0:39:16.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Cape Gannet, a diving bird,\N{\rCHT}塘鵝 一種水鳥{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.79,0:39:18.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,capable of generating speeds of up to\N{\rCHT}飛行速度非常快{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.65,0:39:20.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,75 mph.\N{\rCHT}能達到75公里每小時{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.85,0:39:24.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Turning itself into a missile as it collides with the face of the sea.\N{\rCHT}沖向大海的時候變得像顆導彈一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.98,0:39:30.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Red Head Woodpecker can absorb a G-force of one thousand,\N{\rCHT}這種紅色的啄木鳥能夠吸收1000G的重力加速度{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.98,0:39:34.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,pecking a tree 12 thousand times per day.\N{\rCHT}每天可以啄擊樹幹一萬兩千次{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.15,0:39:37.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,85 million times over it's lifetime.\N{\rCHT}一輩子要啄擊8500萬次{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.00,0:39:43.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Big horned sheep can generate...\N{\rCHT}大角羊可以產生…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.42,0:39:45.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bennet...\N{\rCHT}班尼特…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.30,0:39:48.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay, Okay.\N{\rCHT}好吧 好吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.13,0:39:53.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,All of these animals have shock absorbers.\N{\rCHT}這些動物都有自己的緩衝器{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.13,0:39:55.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,built into their bodies.\N{\rCHT}在它們體內{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.10,0:39:56.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,The woodpeckers tongue\N{\rCHT}啄木鳥的舌頭{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.20,0:39:58.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,extends through the back of the mouth out of the nostril\N{\rCHT}從嘴裡一直延伸到鼻部{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.62,0:40:00.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,encircling the entire cranium.\N{\rCHT}然後環繞了整個頭蓋骨{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.83,0:40:02.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,It is the anatomical equivalent\N{\rCHT}這是解剖可以看到的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.85,0:40:05.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,of a safety belt for it's brain.\N{\rCHT}成了大腦的安全帶{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.71,0:40:10.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Human beings, not a single piece of our anatomy\N{\rCHT}而人類 沒有一次解剖能證明{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.92,0:40:13.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,protects us from those types of collisions.\N{\rCHT}人體記憶體在腦震盪保護器{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.37,0:40:17.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,A human being will get concussed at 60 G's.\N{\rCHT}人體在60倍重力加速度的衝擊力下是會產生腦震盪的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.34,0:40:20.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,A common head to head contact on a football field?\N{\rCHT}橄欖球比賽裡一次普通的頭碰頭的衝擊力有多大？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.75,0:40:24.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,100 G's.\N{\rCHT}100倍重力加速度{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.83,0:40:29.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,God did not intend for us to play football.\N{\rCHT}上帝並沒有給我們打橄欖球的天賦{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.86,0:40:32.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's keep God out of this.\N{\rCHT}別跟我們提上帝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.36,0:40:34.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}好吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.99,0:40:47.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What are S's? - The Steelers.\N{\rCHT}- 一串S是什麼意思？- 匹茲堡鋼人隊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.48,0:40:49.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,- And the O's? - The "others", obviously.\N{\rCHT}- 那一串O又是什麼？- 顯然是別的隊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.63,0:40:51.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, the other team.\N{\rCHT}嗯 別的隊伍{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.71,0:40:54.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Do you even watch football? - No, not at all.\N{\rCHT}- 你看過橄欖球比賽嗎？- 從來沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.97,0:40:57.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,But I've been studying Mike Webster's position.\N{\rCHT}但是我深入瞭解了邁克·韋伯斯特的位置{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.76,0:41:02.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,The man in the middle, is quite deceptively the most violent position on the field.\N{\rCHT}他是個中鋒 這是球場上暴力衝擊最多的位置{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.60,0:41:08.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,The slaps, the punches, the forearm, it is a unremitting storm of sub-concussive blows.\N{\rCHT}推搡 衝撞 肘擊 他無時無刻不承受著這些持續性的打擊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.28,0:41:11.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,The head as a weapon on every single play\N{\rCHT}甚至頭也成了每一個運動員的武器{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.28,0:41:15.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,of every single game, with every single practice, from the time he was a little boy...\N{\rCHT}每一場比賽 每一次練習 從他小時候開始…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.81,0:41:20.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,to a college man, culminating in an 18-year professional career.\N{\rCHT}成為職業球員 18年的職業生涯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.53,0:41:24.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,By my calculations, Mike Webster sustained\N{\rCHT}通過我的計算 我認為邁克·韋伯斯特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.22,0:41:29.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,more than 70,000 blows to his head.\N{\rCHT}遭受了超過七萬次的腦部衝擊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.78,0:41:33.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, these men...\N{\rCHT}現在 這些人…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.89,0:41:36.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,these are the fastest.\N{\rCHT}這些速度最快的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.05,0:41:40.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now their speed, multiplied by the speed of the men who hit them,\N{\rCHT}正在用它們各自速度衝擊著別人和自己的身體{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.85,0:41:46.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,The G Forces generated equivalent to hitting them on the head with a sledgehammer.\N{\rCHT}在它們頭部最終產生的重力加速度就像用大錘在敲打一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.79,0:41:52.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,All of this triggered a cascading series of neurological events,\N{\rCHT}這些因素放在一起引發了一系列的神經問題{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.27,0:41:56.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,which unleashed killer proteins upon Mike Webster's brain.\N{\rCHT}邁克·韋伯斯特的大腦釋放的蛋白質成了殺手{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.39,0:42:01.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Tangles invading and strangling his mind,\N{\rCHT}它們糾纏在一起 影響他的意識{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.81,0:42:03.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,from the inside out.\N{\rCHT}從內到外{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.96,0:42:08.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Like pouring wet concrete down kitchen pipes.\N{\rCHT}就像廚房下水道裡被灌注了混凝土{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.08,0:42:11.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,As it hardens, it chokes the brain,\N{\rCHT}當它凝固的時候 它卡住了大腦{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.08,0:42:14.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,leaving him unrecognizable.\N{\rCHT}讓他記不住事情{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.13,0:42:17.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,Even to himself\N{\rCHT}甚至是他自己{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.25,0:42:21.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't know football, I've ever played.\N{\rCHT}我不瞭解橄欖球 我也沒玩過{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.19,0:42:24.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,But I am telling you\N{\rCHT}但是我現在告訴你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.21,0:42:28.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,That playing football killed Mike Webster.\N{\rCHT}正是橄欖球生涯害死了了邁克·韋伯斯特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.05,0:42:31.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I am certain there are others.\N{\rCHT}同時我敢肯定還會有其他人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.62,0:42:34.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,And how can you possibly know that?\N{\rCHT}你是怎麼知道的？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.04,0:42:39.63,ENG,,0,0,0,,Common sense, but they are either dead or lost in the way Mike Webster was lost.\N{\rCHT}常識 他們要麼會死掉 要麼就是像邁克·韋伯斯特那樣迷失下去{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.66,0:42:42.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not interested in common sense.\N{\rCHT}我對常識不感興趣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.20,0:42:44.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm interested in science.\N{\rCHT}我需要的是科學{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.66,0:42:46.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,And science is knowing.\N{\rCHT}科學才是真理{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.34,0:42:49.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,I know from these players records,\N{\rCHT}我從這些球員記錄得知{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.28,0:42:52.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,that their doctors believe that they have early Alzheimer's,\N{\rCHT}醫生診斷他們是早期阿爾茨海默氏症{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.43,0:42:55.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,which is statistically impossible...\N{\rCHT}從統計學來說是不可能的…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.36,0:42:57.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,they are too young.\N{\rCHT}他們太年輕{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.71,0:43:03.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because it is not Alzheimer's, it is this.\N{\rCHT}因為它不是阿爾茨海默氏症 所以是碰撞造成的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.30,0:43:26.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't like it...\N{\rCHT}我不喜歡這個…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.83,0:43:31.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, actually I hate it.\N{\rCHT}不 其實我討厭這件事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.38,0:43:33.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,But as a scientist...\N{\rCHT}但是作為一個科學家…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.54,0:43:38.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,I can't deny it.\N{\rCHT}我不能睜著眼說瞎話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.52,0:43:42.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Name it. You have to give this a name.\N{\rCHT}它叫什麼 你必須給它取個名字{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.11,0:44:10.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. Did I wake you?\N{\rCHT}抱歉 打擾到你了嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.89,0:44:14.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Did they agree? What it is?\N{\rCHT}他們同意了嗎？結果怎麼樣？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.06,0:44:19.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, we are going to publish.\N{\rCHT}同意了 我們將要公佈了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.90,0:44:24.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,They? with you?\N{\rCHT}他們和你一起？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.18,0:44:26.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, in a medical journal.\N{\rCHT}是的 在一個醫學期刊上{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.32,0:44:32.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,- With you? - Yes, with me, together.\N{\rCHT}- 和你一起？- 是的 和我一起{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.10,0:44:35.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's so...\N{\rCHT}那麼…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.28,0:44:40.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Congratulations. - Thank you, thank you.\N{\rCHT}- 恭喜你 - 謝謝 謝謝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.65,0:44:52.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You... Are you going somewhere? - Yes, with you.\N{\rCHT}- 你… 你要出去嗎？- 是的 和你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.14,0:44:55.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,To celebrate.\N{\rCHT}去慶祝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.88,0:45:14.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,You don't dance, do you?\N{\rCHT}你不跳舞嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.74,0:47:00.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,I had quite a revelation tonight.\N{\rCHT}我今晚有點興奮{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.19,0:47:05.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,This body was made for dancing.\N{\rCHT}這身體就是為跳舞而存在的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.61,0:47:08.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,When they say "dancing machine", I am what they mean.\N{\rCHT}他們說的"跳舞機器" 就是在說我呀{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.60,0:47:14.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am very proud of you.\N{\rCHT}我為你感到驕傲{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.09,0:47:20.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}嗯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.47,0:47:45.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,May I kiss you?\N{\rCHT}我可以吻你嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.46,0:48:34.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Good Morning - Cyril.\N{\rCHT}- 早啊 - 西瑞爾{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.59,0:48:37.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's very weird to bring women into the morgue at night.\N{\rCHT}大晚上的把妹子帶進太平間真是非常詭異啊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.00,0:48:40.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,- She is a friend. - You don't have friends.\N{\rCHT}- 她是個朋友 - 你哪有朋友{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.39,0:48:43.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Listen, Danny knows she's been in there.\N{\rCHT}聽著 丹尼知道她去過{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.72,0:48:46.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's thinking about filing a formal complaint.\N{\rCHT}他準備投訴你了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.25,0:48:49.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,What? I was working on Webster.\N{\rCHT}什麼？我是在工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.23,0:48:51.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,I know, I'll take care of it.\N{\rCHT}我知道 我會解決的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.15,0:48:53.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,How much has that cost you so far?\N{\rCHT}你到現在總共花費了多少錢？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.52,0:48:56.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,- 20,000. - 20?\N{\rCHT}- 兩萬 - 兩萬？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.71,0:48:59.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,I Save, everything.\N{\rCHT}我自己承擔{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.44,0:49:02.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Really? How unamerican.\N{\rCHT}真的？非主流啊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.96,0:49:07.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe it was worth it. I got the call.\N{\rCHT}也許你是對的 我接到了一個電話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.13,0:49:11.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Chronic Traumatic Encephalopathy" got a nice ring to it, doesn't it...\N{\rCHT}"慢性創傷腦部病變"聽起來不錯嘛 是吧…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.34,0:49:13.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, CTE\N{\rCHT}是的 簡稱CTE{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.41,0:49:14.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,So what happens now?\N{\rCHT}那麼到底發生了什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.08,0:49:18.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,We publish, DeKosky is going to co-author.\N{\rCHT}我們發佈出來了 德庫思也是合著者{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.73,0:49:22.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,- DeKosky? - Yes, Omalu DeKosky.\N{\rCHT}- 德庫思？- 是的 奧奧馬魯 德庫思{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.11,0:49:25.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,And Cyril Wecht.\N{\rCHT}還有西瑞爾·威切特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.11,0:49:32.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Well I'm very proud of you. - Thank you.\N{\rCHT}- 好吧 為你感到驕傲 - 謝謝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.91,0:49:35.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,See? The gray is the right colour.\N{\rCHT}看到了嗎？灰色才是最好的顏色{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.43,0:49:37.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Blue shows dirt even in the rain.\N{\rCHT}在雨天裡藍色顯得很容易髒{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.62,0:49:48.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,Let's go, baby.\N{\rCHT}開始吧 夥計們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.70,0:50:13.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Going across...\N{\rCHT}穿過去了…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.75,0:50:17.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Arrgh\N{\rCHT}啊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.76,0:50:31.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I'm hearing voices - Are you serious?\N{\rCHT}- 我聽到有聲音 - 不要緊吧？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.07,0:50:34.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,Justin, stop, you're scaring them.\N{\rCHT}賈斯汀 停下來 你嚇到我了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.42,0:50:35.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look at me\N{\rCHT}看著我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.90,0:50:41.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're telling me to kill you. They're telling me to kill you.\N{\rCHT}他們要我殺了你 殺了你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.13,0:50:47.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get out...\N{\rCHT}滾出去…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.66,0:51:02.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't. Why, God? No...\N{\rCHT}別 上帝啊 不…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.61,0:51:06.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,All units... black pickup spotted...\N{\rCHT}所有單位請注意… 黑色皮卡…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.44,0:51:09.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,I see him, just passing me.\N{\rCHT}我看見了 剛剛超過我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.72,0:51:12.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Reportedly driving into opposite traffic the last 10 miles...\N{\rCHT}我繞到路口過去需要10英里…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.66,0:51:14.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God...\N{\rCHT}我的天啊…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.21,0:51:15.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Pickup has collided.\N{\rCHT}皮卡車爆炸了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.16,0:51:17.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,All units... report\N{\rCHT}所有單位… 上報{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.97,0:51:41.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,A few months after Steeler favourite Justin Strzelczyk was killed in that fiery accident,\N{\rCHT}在鋼人隊最受歡迎的賈斯汀·斯托克斯死於一場交通事故的幾個月後{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.83,0:51:46.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yet another Steelers favourite Terry Long, has apparently committed suicide\N{\rCHT}另一個鋼人隊最受歡迎的球員特裡·隆 也被發現自殺身亡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.81,0:51:47.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,at the age of 45.\N{\rCHT}今年45歲{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.94,0:51:52.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, Terry, You wondered where they are now, now we know.\N{\rCHT}好吧 特裡 你想知道他們在哪裡 現在我們知道了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.04,0:51:56.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,Terry Long, Pittsburgh Steelers.\N{\rCHT}特裡·隆 匹茲堡鋼人隊隊員{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.69,0:51:59.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,I guess these guys only die when you're working.\N{\rCHT}我覺得這些傢伙只在你工作的時候死去{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.45,0:52:01.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,What other problems did he have?\N{\rCHT}他有什麼其他的問題？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.24,0:52:05.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Arrested a few times, fraud, federal theft.\N{\rCHT}被逮捕過幾次 欺詐 盜竊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.55,0:52:07.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wow, arrested a lot.\N{\rCHT}噢 多次被捕{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.63,0:52:10.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,I need a full autopsy, same tests as Mike Webster.\N{\rCHT}我需要做完整的解剖 像邁克·韋伯斯特那樣的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.84,0:52:14.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You paying for that too? - Yes, Danny, I'm paying for that too.\N{\rCHT}- 你自己支付費用嗎？- 是的 丹尼 我支付{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.29,0:52:22.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Joseph Maroon.\N{\rCHT}約瑟夫·馬路恩{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.91,0:53:21.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is my dream.\N{\rCHT}這是我的理想{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.28,0:53:26.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,The schools are good.\N{\rCHT}這些學校很好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.04,0:53:30.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,You are good, Prema.\N{\rCHT}你也很好 普蕾瑪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.70,0:53:36.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you see good in me.\N{\rCHT}我相信你也能看到我的好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.22,0:53:41.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,I see all that you are.\N{\rCHT}我懂{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.70,0:53:46.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,I want to marry you.\N{\rCHT}我想要娶你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.63,0:53:51.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,We can fall in love...\N{\rCHT}讓我們在愛河裡徜徉…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.51,0:54:03.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you want to marry me, I will marry you.\N{\rCHT}如果你要娶我 我就嫁給你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.96,0:54:08.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,That is good because I already made the down payment.\N{\rCHT}太好了 我已經付過首付了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.04,0:54:17.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,I saved all my money and I bought this for you.\N{\rCHT}我用我所有的錢為你買下它{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.97,0:54:59.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get me Elliot Pellman.\N{\rCHT}幫我接接艾略特·帕爾曼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.79,0:55:16.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,I have Chris Jones for you.\N{\rCHT}克裡斯·鐘斯讓我叫你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.71,0:55:19.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm just looking at it.\N{\rCHT}我正在看{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.64,0:55:22.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Anything to be concerned about?\N{\rCHT}有什麼需要關注的嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.73,0:55:26.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,This Omalu, he's a coroner in Pittsburgh.\N{\rCHT}這個奧瑪魯是匹茲堡的一個驗屍官{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.06,0:55:28.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,He looks like a nobody, but... let me get into it.\N{\rCHT}看起來是個無名小卒 但是… 讓我調查一下{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.88,0:55:51.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hello? - Is Bennet Omalu there?\N{\rCHT}- 你好 - 是班尼特·奧奧馬魯家嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.20,0:55:53.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes, he is.\N{\rCHT}呃 是的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.80,0:55:55.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay, yes?\N{\rCHT}嗯 你是？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.93,0:55:58.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm a neurologist who's worked around football for years.\N{\rCHT}我是一個做橄欖球相關研究很多年的神經學家{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.11,0:56:02.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Very familiar with the NFL's concussion research.\N{\rCHT}對美國職業橄欖球聯盟的腦震盪研究非常瞭解{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.17,0:56:03.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,And the League concluded unequivocally that\N{\rCHT}聯盟的明確結論是{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.90,0:56:07.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,football players do not get brain damage.\N{\rCHT}橄欖球球員並不會得腦損傷{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.07,0:56:09.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,Webster was one random case, Mr.Omalu.\N{\rCHT}韋伯斯特是個偶然事件 奧瑪魯先生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.00,0:56:12.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Doctor Omalu. - Well, whatever.\N{\rCHT}- 是奧奧馬魯醫生 - 隨你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.44,0:56:15.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're an uneducated quack and your career is over.\N{\rCHT}你是一個無知的庸醫 你的職業生涯就要結束了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.93,0:56:22.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,They said you were uneducated? Did they even read your resume?\N{\rCHT}他們說你是文盲嗎？他們沒有看過你的簡歷嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.98,0:56:24.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well I got calls too.\N{\rCHT}好吧 我也有電話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.96,0:56:28.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,Apparently the National Football League owns neuroscience.\N{\rCHT}顯然美國國家橄欖球聯盟擁有自己的神經科學醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.61,0:56:31.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Who knew? - Failure to find\N{\rCHT}- 是誰？- 沒找到{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.47,0:56:34.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,absence of clinical information.\N{\rCHT}臨床資訊的缺乏{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.32,0:56:36.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What do they want? - Your head on a spike.\N{\rCHT}- 他們想怎樣？- 懲罰你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.98,0:56:41.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,- They want you to retract your findings. - They want you to say you made it all up.\N{\rCHT}- 他們希望你收回你的言論 - 他們想要你說你虛構了這一切{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.93,0:56:45.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I made it up? - They're accusing you of fraud.\N{\rCHT}- 我虛構的嗎？- 他們要指控你有欺詐行為{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.01,0:56:48.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you retract, you'll be fine.\N{\rCHT}如果你收回言論 你會沒事的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.73,0:56:50.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,This all goes away.\N{\rCHT}這一切也就沒有意義了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.93,0:56:54.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Why are they doing this? - They're terrified of you.\N{\rCHT}- 他們為什麼這麼做？- 他們害怕你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.51,0:56:57.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,What'd you think they were gonna say? "Thank you"?\N{\rCHT}你以為他們會說什麼？"謝謝"？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.24,0:56:59.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yes. - What the hell for?\N{\rCHT}- 是的 - 為什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.20,0:57:02.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,For being told. For knowing.\N{\rCHT}為了知情權 為了真理{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.61,0:57:08.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,I understand. You think you're being a good American.\N{\rCHT}我明白 你覺得你在做好一個美國公民{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.22,0:57:15.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,So... the city of Pittsburgh spent $233 million\N{\rCHT}呃… 匹茲堡城市花了2.33億美元{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.28,0:57:19.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,to build their glorious Steelers a new stadium.\N{\rCHT}建造了他們的引以為傲的新鋼人體育場{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.51,0:57:22.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,All the while they were closing schools,\N{\rCHT}他們關閉學校{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.17,0:57:24.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,and raising taxes.\N{\rCHT}提高稅收{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.35,0:57:27.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,These people are not out to change the world.\N{\rCHT}這些人並不是要改變世界{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.02,0:57:32.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,And this is not some quaint academic discovery\N{\rCHT}這也不是附在一本名不見經傳的醫學期刊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.84,0:57:35.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,stuck in the back of an obscure medical journal.\N{\rCHT}後面的奇怪的學術發現{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.05,0:57:41.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bennet Omalu is going to war with a corporation\N{\rCHT}班尼特·奧奧馬魯是要與一個集團展開一場鬥爭{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.07,0:57:44.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,That has 20 million people on a weekly basis\N{\rCHT}他們每週有20萬人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.04,0:57:45.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,craving their product.\N{\rCHT}在期待著他們的比賽{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.05,0:57:48.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,The same way they crave food.\N{\rCHT}像期待將要上桌的飯菜{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.47,0:57:52.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,The NFL owns a day of the week.\N{\rCHT}美國職業橄欖球聯盟佔據著一周中的一天{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.17,0:57:58.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,The same day the church used to own, now it's theirs.\N{\rCHT}就像以前的教堂一樣 不過現在橄欖球是人們的信仰{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.11,0:58:00.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're very big.\N{\rCHT}他們很強大{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.09,0:58:15.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Terry Long.\N{\rCHT}特裡·隆{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.77,0:58:20.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,His tests came back positive.\N{\rCHT}他的測試結果呈陽性{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.23,0:58:26.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Football gave him CTE, and CTE told his brain\N{\rCHT}橄欖球造成了腦震盪 腦震盪損傷了大腦{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.75,0:58:31.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,to drink a gallon of antifreeze and he died.\N{\rCHT}他喝了一桶防凍液就自殺了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.88,0:58:34.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,I told you there would be more.\N{\rCHT}我說過會有更多人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.74,0:58:38.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,You have done great work.\N{\rCHT}你已經做了很偉大的工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.43,0:58:41.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,No one would blame you if you stopped now.\N{\rCHT}你就算現在放棄也沒人會怪你的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.32,0:58:43.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,No one is stopping anything.\N{\rCHT}沒人會放棄的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.67,0:58:46.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then I'd be lying if I didn't tell you\N{\rCHT}可能我不說的話就是自欺欺人了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.00,0:58:49.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,how important your next move is.\N{\rCHT}你接下來做的事情非常重要{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.19,0:59:00.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,By the time Terry Long committed suicide,\N{\rCHT}特裡·隆自殺的時候{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.09,0:59:04.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,his brain had been consumed by Chronic Traumatic Encephalopathy.\N{\rCHT}他的大腦早已經得了慢性創傷腦部病變{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.95,0:59:07.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,And it is probable, perhaps even likely,\N{\rCHT}甚至有可能{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.93,0:59:11.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,that a large percentage of professional football players,\N{\rCHT}大部分的職業球員{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.14,0:59:13.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,have and will die from CTE.\N{\rCHT}都會死於慢性創傷腦部病變{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.76,0:59:17.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,This was the Pittsburgh medical examiner's own, Dr.Bennet Omalu.\N{\rCHT}這是匹茲堡的法醫 班尼特·奧奧馬魯醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.28,0:59:20.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who today threw down the gauntlet at the feet of the National Football League.\N{\rCHT}今天發起了對美國國家橄欖球聯盟的挑戰{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.99,0:59:22.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\N{\rCHT}謝謝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.96,0:59:29.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What do you think? - I think you're gonna be an American hero.\N{\rCHT}- 你覺得怎麼樣？- 我想你會成為一個美國英雄的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.72,0:59:33.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I'm not even an American. - Ah, that's even better.\N{\rCHT}- 我甚至不是一個土生土長的美國人 - 呃 那樣更好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.70,0:59:36.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's so fucking American\N{\rCHT}去他娘的美國人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.79,0:59:40.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,Doctor Maroon,\N{\rCHT}馬路恩醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.11,0:59:44.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,who is also vice chairman of the neuro-surgery department\N{\rCHT}神經學會副主席{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.07,0:59:46.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,At the University of Pittsburghin Medical Centre ,\N{\rCHT}就職于匹茲堡大學醫學中心{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.50,0:59:49.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,said of Omalu's CTE diagnosis:\N{\rCHT}聲稱奧瑪魯的腦部慢性病變診斷{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.71,0:59:53.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,That it was fallacious reasoning.\N{\rCHT}荒謬至極{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.02,1:00:04.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yes. - Is this Bennet Omalu?\N{\rCHT}- 你好 - 是班尼特·奧奧馬魯嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.26,1:00:06.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,Doctor Bennet Omalu.\N{\rCHT}是班尼特·奧奧馬魯醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.38,1:00:08.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,You want to pussify this country?\N{\rCHT}你他媽想搞亂這個國家？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.40,1:00:13.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,You want to vaginise football? Get the hell out, or they'll be doing your autopsy.\N{\rCHT}你他媽要搞死橄欖球嗎？滾遠點 否則被解剖的就是你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.64,1:01:11.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Dr.Omalu? - Yes?.\N{\rCHT}- 奧瑪魯醫生？- 怎麼了？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.26,1:01:16.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,I took you to be an early riser, I didn't want to call you at your office.\N{\rCHT}我猜你是個早起的人 我不想打到你辦公室{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.86,1:01:22.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,- This is Julian Bailes, do you know who I am? - I know who you are.\N{\rCHT}- 我是是朱利安·貝爾斯 你認識我嗎？- 認識{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.02,1:01:26.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mike Webster was a personal friend.\N{\rCHT}邁克·韋伯斯特曾經是我的好朋友{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.70,1:01:29.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,Was he?\N{\rCHT}是嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.00,1:01:34.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dr.Omalu, you're in trouble but you're not wrong.\N{\rCHT}奧瑪魯醫生 你雖然有麻煩但是你並沒有做錯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.11,1:01:37.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,I would like to talk with you.\N{\rCHT}我想和你談談{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.39,1:02:11.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,The NFL has known about this concussion crisis for years.\N{\rCHT}國家橄欖球聯盟多年來一直知道腦震盪對人的影響{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.13,1:02:13.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,What you have there is the research,\N{\rCHT}這些是調查報告{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.61,1:02:17.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,that forms the basis for the league's concussion guidelines.\N{\rCHT}是聯盟對腦震盪調查方向的指南{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.31,1:02:21.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,In this study, some academics put helmets on monkeys,\N{\rCHT}在研究的時候 一些專家給猴子戴上頭盔{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.49,1:02:24.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,And shook them real hard, they threw dogs and pigs...\N{\rCHT}去進行猛烈地撞擊 還有狗和豬…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.74,1:02:27.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,and human cadavers down elevator shafts.\N{\rCHT}還有人類屍體的升降落體實驗{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.65,1:02:30.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Helmets on crash test dummies and bashed them together.\N{\rCHT}實驗人體和頭盔在一起碰撞形成衝擊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.81,1:02:33.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,And their conclusion?\N{\rCHT}他們的結論是？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.39,1:02:40.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,"No striking player experienced neck injury or concussion."\N{\rCHT}沒球員有明顯的頸部受傷或腦震盪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.34,1:02:43.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,So a concussion is no more dangerous than a hangnail.\N{\rCHT}所以腦震盪甚至沒有手指頭的倒拉刺危險{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.57,1:02:45.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,- And that was it? - Oh, no, no, no.\N{\rCHT}- 就那樣了？- 哦 不不不{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.04,1:02:48.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,The NFL did what every organization does.\N{\rCHT}NFL作為一個聯盟{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.78,1:02:52.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,They put together a commission to study the study: "Dr.Elliot Pellman's\N{\rCHT}他們組成了一個委員會由艾略特醫生帶頭的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.81,1:02:55.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mild Traumatic Brain committee".\N{\rCHT}"輕度腦創傷性委員會"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.18,1:02:56.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know who else was on that committee?\N{\rCHT}你知道還有誰在這個委員會嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.99,1:02:57.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dr.Moroon Joe.\N{\rCHT}魔力紅醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.87,1:03:00.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he was on there, plus a couple of others.\N{\rCHT}是的 有他 當然還有其它人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.64,1:03:06.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Team doctors, an equipment manager and two trainers.\N{\rCHT}醫生團隊 一個經理 兩個教練{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.45,1:03:08.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Guys who tape knees for a living, I mean\N{\rCHT}我意思是大家其實都很難做{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.42,1:03:25.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why am I here, Dr.Bailes?\N{\rCHT}請我來這幹什麼 貝爾斯醫生？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.64,1:03:28.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Doctor, I'm not with the Steelers anymore.\N{\rCHT}醫生 我跟鋼人隊沒有一點關係了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.64,1:03:32.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not with the NFL.\N{\rCHT}我也不在國家橄欖球聯盟工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.27,1:03:37.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now... Do you know how many Pittsburgh Steelers,\N{\rCHT}現在… 你知道有多少個鋼人隊的球員{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.61,1:03:41.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,just Steelers now, have died in the last few years?\N{\rCHT}只是鋼人隊 在過去的幾年裡死了的？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.59,1:03:45.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I'm not talking about the older guys, I'm talking about men that I worked with.\N{\rCHT}我們不討論更早期的了 只討論一下我這一撥的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.05,1:03:47.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,And just the ones I know about.\N{\rCHT}就我知道的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.64,1:03:50.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,Twelve.\N{\rCHT}有12個{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.80,1:03:54.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I don't wanna see any more of these men vanish\N{\rCHT}我不想看到越來越多的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.00,1:03:57.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,in the back of a pickup truck.\N{\rCHT}重蹈賈斯汀的覆轍而消失{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.08,1:04:13.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,I know them, I was them.\N{\rCHT}我瞭解他們 我跟他們一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.88,1:04:15.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I think you're doing this wrong.\N{\rCHT}我認為你這樣做是錯誤的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.88,1:04:18.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,As long as the NFL continues to deny the truth,\N{\rCHT}只要國家橄欖球聯盟繼續否認事實{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.79,1:04:19.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,nothing changes.\N{\rCHT}什麼都不會改變{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.80,1:04:21.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's only true if they say it's true.\N{\rCHT}他們說是真的才是真的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.80,1:04:24.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,And they gotta say it out loud.\N{\rCHT}他們還得公開地承認這一點{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.48,1:04:26.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get me a meeting with the commissioner.\N{\rCHT}讓我和委員們見一面{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.79,1:04:30.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,I want to sit with him man to man, face to face. I will make him say it out loud\N{\rCHT}我要這這些人面對面 我要讓他們大聲說出真相{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.62,1:04:33.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,They don't wanna talk to you.\N{\rCHT}他們不想和你見面{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.92,1:04:36.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Football does not want to talk to you.\N{\rCHT}橄欖球不想跟你妥協{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.87,1:04:41.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Like my daddy, a Louisiana Judge always used to say to me: "Son,\N{\rCHT}我的父親 路易斯安那的法官 他總是對我說{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.54,1:04:45.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,God is number one, and football is number two".\N{\rCHT}上帝排第一位 橄欖球排在第二位{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.07,1:04:52.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Besides to them, you're not even American, You're not even African American.\N{\rCHT}而且 你還不是是美國人 甚至不是非裔美國人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.24,1:04:55.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're...\N{\rCHT}你…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.78,1:04:57.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,A doctor?\N{\rCHT}只是個醫生？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.95,1:05:03.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Okay.\N{\rCHT}好吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.69,1:05:09.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look... the league has kept everyone in the dark.\N{\rCHT}聯盟一直將真相隱藏在黑暗中{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.17,1:05:11.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,And you turned on the lights and gave\N{\rCHT}現在你打開了聚光燈{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.18,1:05:13.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,their biggest Boogeyman a name.\N{\rCHT}說出了他們的秘密{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.59,1:05:15.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's happening now?\N{\rCHT}現在是什麼狀況？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.50,1:05:18.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,What you think they're doing to you? That's nothing.\N{\rCHT}你覺得他們會對你做什麼嗎？沒什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.12,1:05:25.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,I've done my own research, on this "NFL Brain Injury Committee".\N{\rCHT}我已經調查了這個"國家橄欖球聯盟腦損傷研究小組"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.52,1:05:30.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know what Dr.Elliot Pellman is? He's a rheumatologist.\N{\rCHT}你知道艾略特·佩爾曼醫生時幹什麼的嗎？他是一個風濕病學家{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.24,1:05:33.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,He's a specialist in arthritis and joint pain.\N{\rCHT}他的專業是關節炎和關節疼痛{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.31,1:05:36.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Can you tell me, what a rheumatologist knows\N{\rCHT}你能告訴我風濕病學家知道什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.73,1:05:38.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,about the brain and brain disease?\N{\rCHT}關於大腦和大腦疾病的東西？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.39,1:05:44.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,Corporate men like this, in this country, usually go to Harvard or Yale.\N{\rCHT}在這個國家 這樣的人通常應該去哈佛或耶魯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.30,1:05:48.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,He went to medical school in Guadalajara.\N{\rCHT}他去了在瓜達拉哈拉的醫學院{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.55,1:05:51.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Mexico? - Yes.\N{\rCHT}- 墨西哥的？- 是的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.91,1:05:53.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,I did not know that.\N{\rCHT}我不知道{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.27,1:05:57.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,That's beautiful.\N{\rCHT}那很美{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.22,1:06:05.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,Now, two cases does not meet the scientific burden of proof.\N{\rCHT}現在 有兩個案例不滿足科學的舉證責任{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.66,1:06:08.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,You have to keep going.\N{\rCHT}你必須堅持住{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.03,1:06:14.08,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just so you understand, this does not show up on a CT scan.\N{\rCHT}正如你發現的 問題並不能在CT影像上呈現{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.12,1:06:16.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,Which means there is no diagnosis before death.\N{\rCHT}這就意味著死之前沒法診斷出來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.71,1:06:19.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,In order for me to keep going...\N{\rCHT}我要堅持下去的話…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.26,1:06:20.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,more have to die.\N{\rCHT}得有更多人死去{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.13,1:06:23.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, that's already happening.\N{\rCHT}不幸的是 這已經發生了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.61,1:07:10.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Double D. Did I hear right we're losing you?\N{\rCHT}我沒聽錯吧？聽說你要走了？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.48,1:07:12.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tapping you for mayor of Chicago?\N{\rCHT}去芝加哥做市長？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.57,1:07:14.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,Still a long, long road, my friend.\N{\rCHT}還差很遠呢{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.80,1:07:18.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,All world killer athlete to civilian to king...\N{\rCHT}世界殺手級運動員 在一生中{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.22,1:07:20.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,all in one lifetime, ladies and gentlemen...\N{\rCHT}從平民到國王 女士們先生們…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.80,1:07:25.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,I give you Mayor Dave Duerson, who has figured it out\N{\rCHT}能搞定一切的戴夫·杜爾森當選市長{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.77,1:07:31.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Dave - Yeah?\N{\rCHT}- 戴夫 - 有事嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.47,1:07:33.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's me man. Andre Waters.\N{\rCHT}是我 安德魯·瓦特斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.47,1:07:34.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,How're you doing, man?\N{\rCHT}你最近怎麼樣？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.43,1:07:37.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look, let me walk with you.\N{\rCHT}我跟你走走吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.32,1:07:40.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's not good, Dave, not good.\N{\rCHT}不好 戴夫 很不好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.45,1:07:44.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,You've seen the paperwork, why's the committee doing this, man?\N{\rCHT}你看過檔了吧 委員會怎麼能這麼做？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.70,1:07:47.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,There are 5 other trustees, you talk to them?\N{\rCHT}還有5個其他受託人 你和他們談了嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.31,1:07:50.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,You the only one who played, man, You the only one who knows what it is to be us.\N{\rCHT}你是唯一和我們接觸的人 你是唯一瞭解我們的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.63,1:07:53.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, hey, hey. You and me, we were the same man.\N{\rCHT}喂 喂 喂 喂 你和我 我們是一類的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.72,1:07:55.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,Huh? We were bangers, hitmen.\N{\rCHT}我們是炸彈 是殺手{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:55.59,1:07:57.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,File the appeal\N{\rCHT}拿檔去上訴{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.79,1:08:01.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,You denied the appeal, Dave Look, somethings wrong with me man.\N{\rCHT}你駁回了上訴 戴夫 你看 我們這些人身上是有問題的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.42,1:08:05.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,I can't sleep, I mean my eyes get crossed It wears me out... Hey.\N{\rCHT}我睡不著 我是說我眼睛合上了又被弄開… 喂{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.85,1:08:07.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Look at me man. - Jesus!\N{\rCHT}- 看著我 - 我的天{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.34,1:08:11.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Twelve years I payed my dues. I made millions for those assholes.\N{\rCHT}我交了十二年的稅 幫那些混蛋賺了幾百萬{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.22,1:08:13.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Come on, just lend me your money, man.\N{\rCHT}拜託 借我點錢吧 夥計{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.93,1:08:15.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just asking back what I gave.\N{\rCHT}就當做還我一個人情了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.04,1:08:20.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Listen, FAT, stop eating like a pig. Got a headache? See a doctor.\N{\rCHT}聽著 肥豬 別像個豬一樣不停地吃了 頭痛嗎？去找醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.09,1:08:23.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,I've seen 20 doctors. I just need rent money.\N{\rCHT}我已經看了20個醫生了 我需要借點錢{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.22,1:08:25.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Get your shit together.\N{\rCHT}滾遠點{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.21,1:08:28.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,You used to be a warrior.\N{\rCHT}你曾是個勇士{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.04,1:08:30.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You fucking sellout. - Get your hands off me.\N{\rCHT}- 你這個叛徒 - 把你的手拿開{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.92,1:08:33.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm Sorry, Dave, I'm sorry.\N{\rCHT}對不起 戴夫 對不起{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.26,1:08:37.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,Look, Hey, Hey, Remember when we were kids?\N{\rCHT}還記得我們小時候嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.77,1:08:40.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Playing's what we live for, huh?\N{\rCHT}我們一起生活一起玩耍{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.85,1:08:43.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,I need your help...\N{\rCHT}我需要你的説明…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.74,1:08:49.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dave, help me\N{\rCHT}戴夫 救救我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.30,1:09:06.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Andre Waters, known as "Dirty Water", notorious for his aggressive style of play,\N{\rCHT}安德魯·瓦特斯 綽號"髒水" 他的進攻風格粗暴醜陋{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.42,1:09:09.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,and devastating hits that filled highlight reels.\N{\rCHT}最有名的是他具有毀滅性的兇猛擒抱{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.05,1:09:13.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Waters died of a self-inflicted gunshot wound to the head.\N{\rCHT}瓦特斯吞槍自殺{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.85,1:09:16.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,He was 44.\N{\rCHT}終年44歲{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.31,1:09:23.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,And uh, this is the part where he uh...\N{\rCHT}呃 這只是一部分{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.83,1:09:27.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,He got knocked out.\N{\rCHT}他犯滿離場{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.80,1:09:32.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,He said he was alright.\N{\rCHT}他說自己沒事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.82,1:09:36.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,He was maybe just a little dazed, but he said he was alright.\N{\rCHT}他也許只是有點眩暈 但他說自己沒問題{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.98,1:09:42.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,You look well.\N{\rCHT}你看起來氣色不錯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.46,1:09:46.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,- How are the kids? - Kids are fine.\N{\rCHT}- 孩子們怎麼樣？-孩子們很好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.25,1:09:49.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.\N{\rCHT}我也很好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.06,1:09:54.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I couldn't make it to the funeral.\N{\rCHT}對不起 我沒能參加他的葬禮{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.98,1:09:58.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,No one made it to the funeral.\N{\rCHT}沒人必須去參加的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.80,1:10:03.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,He was the sun, we was the planets.\N{\rCHT}他是太陽 我們是行星{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.21,1:10:10.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,And then, after he give me this card he said: "Mom...\N{\rCHT}然後 他給我這張卡片後說:"媽媽…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.83,1:10:17.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm ready to go. "\N{\rCHT}我要走了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.32,1:10:20.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because he knew that people was thinking he was crazy.\N{\rCHT}因為他知道人們都認為他瘋了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.85,1:10:28.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not crazy, he had already become someone else.\N{\rCHT}他沒瘋 他只不過變成其它人了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.10,1:10:34.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,You definitely think he had this disease? Because I want to believe that.\N{\rCHT}你真的認為他是得了這種病嗎？我希望是這樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.59,1:10:37.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,I believe so, yes.\N{\rCHT}我相信是這樣的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.08,1:10:42.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,And now you want what's left of my boy.\N{\rCHT}你還想知道我的孩子留下了什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.17,1:10:47.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,You heard about Mike Webster?\N{\rCHT}你知道邁克·韋伯斯特嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.42,1:10:55.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,And Terry Long and... and who else?\N{\rCHT}還有特裡·隆 還有… 還有其他人嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.81,1:11:02.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,What do you really want to ask me, Julian?\N{\rCHT}你到底想問我什麼 朱利安？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.52,1:11:34.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dr.Cyril Wecht, Dr.Julian Bailes.\N{\rCHT}西瑞爾·威切特醫生 朱利安·貝爾斯醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.23,1:11:37.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,Pleasure to meet you.\N{\rCHT}很高興見到你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.47,1:11:44.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,Andre Waters.\N{\rCHT}安德魯·瓦特斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.20,1:11:55.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Justin Strzelczyk.\N{\rCHT}賈斯汀·斯托克斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.10,1:12:10.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I just kept sending them back out there.\N{\rCHT}我只是不停地送走他們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.66,1:12:13.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,What the hell were you thinking?\N{\rCHT}你到底在想些什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.75,1:12:16.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,You gotta be a part of it, you gotta be...\N{\rCHT}你必須和他們在一起 你應該…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.93,1:12:19.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,On the sidelines with them to understand.\N{\rCHT}得站在他們的角度去理解問題{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.15,1:12:24.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Whatever it takes to keep them in the game, To keep the whole thing going.\N{\rCHT}無論它們在比賽中的表現怎麼樣 都得堅持下去{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.74,1:12:30.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tape, Needles, Vicodin, Toradol, Lidocaine, Percocet,\N{\rCHT}膠帶 針頭 維柯丁 酮咯酸 利多卡因 撲熱息痛{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.36,1:12:32.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,Lexapro, Zoloft.\N{\rCHT}依地普林 郁樂複{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.09,1:12:36.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Have I left anything out?\N{\rCHT}我有漏了說什麼嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.72,1:12:38.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's Tyres and oil.\N{\rCHT}這些就像是輪胎和汽油{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.99,1:12:41.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's mechanics trying to keep the cars on the racetrack.\N{\rCHT}是讓汽車在賽道上賓士的動力保障{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.59,1:12:45.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah, well, it's not medicine... I don't know what it is.\N{\rCHT}好吧 不是醫學… 我不知道是什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.28,1:12:48.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's business.\N{\rCHT}是生意{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.89,1:12:52.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Oh, There you go. - Okay, Okay.\N{\rCHT}- 隨你便了 - 好了 好了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.34,1:12:56.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,Three cases, is the scientific burden of evidence.\N{\rCHT}3個案例 才能支撐科學證據{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.90,1:12:59.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,We have 4. That is far beyond anything.\N{\rCHT}我們有4個 這比任何事情都重要{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.84,1:13:01.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,The NFL can or cannot deny.\N{\rCHT}不管國家橄欖球聯盟承認與否{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.66,1:13:03.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is bigger than they are.\N{\rCHT}這都比他們更厲害{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.41,1:13:07.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,They have to listen to us now.\N{\rCHT}他們現在應該聽我們的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.21,1:13:28.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dr.Moroon, would you like a drink?\N{\rCHT}魔力紅醫生 你想喝點什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.45,1:13:31.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I said 5 minutes. - He doesn't want a drink.\N{\rCHT}- 我說了只有5分鐘時間 - 他不想喝東西{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.68,1:13:35.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your conclusions totally misrepresent the facts.\N{\rCHT}你的結論完全是在歪曲事實{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.41,1:13:39.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,To say that Webster, Long and Waters were killed by football is just...\N{\rCHT}所謂的韋伯斯特 隆 和瓦特斯是被橄欖球殺死的全都是…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.40,1:13:43.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Fallacious reasoning. Yes, I know.\N{\rCHT}錯誤的推理 是的 我知道{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.89,1:13:47.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Where is he going with this?\N{\rCHT}他這是要幹嘛？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:47.34,1:13:49.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just hear him out.\N{\rCHT}聽他說完{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:49.91,1:13:56.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,I would like to propose a formal, controlled study of former and current...\N{\rCHT}我想發起一個正式的 可控制的對於國家橄欖球聯盟{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.09,1:13:57.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,NFL football players.\N{\rCHT}現役和前成員的研究{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.82,1:14:01.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,We will bring together the greatest minds in America\N{\rCHT}讓我們一起給這個國家帶來偉大的思想{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:01.14,1:14:04.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,To solve the problem. We should be working together.\N{\rCHT}我們應該一起努力去解決這個問題{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.05,1:14:09.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who do you think you're talking to?\N{\rCHT}你以為你在跟誰說話？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.25,1:14:11.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,Excuse me?\N{\rCHT}什麼意思？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.48,1:14:15.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,I was the president of the congress of neurological surgeons.\N{\rCHT}我以前是神經外科醫協會的主席{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.28,1:14:19.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I was the man who performed the autopsies, on Mike Webster\N{\rCHT}我是給邁克·韋伯斯特做屍檢的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.56,1:14:23.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Terry Long, your men.\N{\rCHT}特裡·隆 你的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.22,1:14:27.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Men under your care.\N{\rCHT}歸你照看的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.85,1:14:31.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you know what Mike Webster's wife said?\N{\rCHT}你知道邁克·韋伯斯特的妻子說了什麼嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.57,1:14:37.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,She said, that if she had known that Mike was sick,\N{\rCHT}她說 如果她知道邁克有病的話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.17,1:14:41.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,She would have done more for him.\N{\rCHT}她該為他做更多的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.02,1:14:47.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,But he died. In disgrace.\N{\rCHT}但是他死了 周圍的人都討厭他{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.07,1:14:53.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,Your man.\N{\rCHT}你的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.24,1:14:55.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,You took an oath.\N{\rCHT}你發過誓的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.77,1:14:57.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Tell the truth. - The truth?\N{\rCHT}- 說出真相 - 真相？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.78,1:14:58.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell the truth.\N{\rCHT}把真相說出來吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.84,1:15:05.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,The truth is that the NFL is a blessing and a salvation, my friend.\N{\rCHT}真相就是美國橄欖球聯盟是崇高的 朋友{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.18,1:15:09.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,We employ hundreds of thousands of people.\N{\rCHT}我們提供成千上萬的崗位{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.60,1:15:14.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,We send thousands and thousands of poor kids, to school.\N{\rCHT}我們幫助成千上萬的貧困孩子走進學校{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.19,1:15:18.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,The ownership of this football club has donated millions of dollars\N{\rCHT}這些橄欖球俱樂部拿出成千上萬的美元{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.01,1:15:20.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,to countless charities.\N{\rCHT}成立慈善機構{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.61,1:15:22.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you want me to go on?\N{\rCHT}你想讓我繼續講下去嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.35,1:15:25.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,- That won't be necessary. - Oh, it is necessary.\N{\rCHT}- 那都不重要 - 很重要{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.60,1:15:30.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Football is the most popular sport in America.\N{\rCHT}橄欖球是美國最流行的運動{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.35,1:15:34.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because it is so god damn fantastic.\N{\rCHT}因為這項運動太他媽的不可思議了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.66,1:15:39.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,And that, right there...\N{\rCHT}還有 就在那兒…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.14,1:15:44.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,That is the beating heart of this city.\N{\rCHT}那兒就是這個城市的心臟{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.48,1:15:46.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,And you want to what? end it?\N{\rCHT}而你想幹什麼？消滅它？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.85,1:15:50.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,You want to fold up the National Football League?\N{\rCHT}你想搞垮全國橄欖球聯賽？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.36,1:15:53.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,I want to solve the problem.\N{\rCHT}我想解決問題{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.73,1:15:55.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,Who are you?\N{\rCHT}你憑什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.68,1:16:00.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What are you asking? - You're a pathologist, you perform autopsies.\N{\rCHT}- 你這是什麼意思？- 你是一個病理學家 驗屍官{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.62,1:16:04.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am a mere pathologist. That's it, that's all I am.\N{\rCHT}對 我是個驗屍官 是的 這就是我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.79,1:16:16.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Do you have any idea the impact of what you're doing? - Yes, I do.\N{\rCHT}- 你知道你正在做的事會造成什麼影響嗎？- 當然 我知道{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.47,1:16:20.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you understand the impact of what you are doing?\N{\rCHT}你知道你正在做的事會造成什麼影響嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.28,1:16:24.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,If just 10% of the mothers in America decide that\N{\rCHT}如果有10%的美國母親認為{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.35,1:16:26.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,football is too dangerous for their son's to play...\N{\rCHT}橄欖球太過危險而不讓孩子們去玩…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.97,1:16:30.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,That is it. It is the end of football.\N{\rCHT}這樣的話 橄欖球完蛋了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.64,1:16:36.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Kids, Colleges and eventually it's just a matter of time, The professional game.\N{\rCHT}孩子們 學校和職業體育完蛋只是時間問題了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.24,1:16:39.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,Joe, he does autopsies. He's not in the outcome business.\N{\rCHT}喬 他做屍體解剖 他不分析商業結果{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.00,1:16:42.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,He has no business.\N{\rCHT}他不考慮商業{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.30,1:16:45.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you know what history does to people?\N{\rCHT}你知道歷史對人的影響嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.81,1:16:49.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Trained physicians who ignore science...\N{\rCHT}那些訓練有素的醫生忽視科學…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.92,1:16:52.42,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Oh, wow... - Sir, I am not done.\N{\rCHT}- 哦 哇… - 先生 我不會逃避{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:52.45,1:16:54.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,History laughs.\N{\rCHT}歷史的笑料{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.56,1:17:01.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you continue to deny my work, the world will deny my work.\N{\rCHT}如果你繼續否認我的工作 世界將會否認我的工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.68,1:17:07.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,But men, your men...\N{\rCHT}但是人 你的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.41,1:17:12.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,continue to die. Their families left in ruins.\N{\rCHT}會繼續死去 家庭因而破碎{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.45,1:17:18.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell the truth.\N{\rCHT}把真相說出來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.24,1:17:22.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell the truth.\N{\rCHT}說出來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.26,1:17:35.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,You sure, You sure you want to do this?\N{\rCHT}你確定 你確定想要這麼做？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.96,1:17:39.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,I would ask you that same question, Dr.Moroon.\N{\rCHT}同樣的問題我問問你 魔力紅醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.73,1:17:47.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Oh, your study. I'll get back to you.\N{\rCHT}嗯 你的研究 我會回復你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.77,1:18:02.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, that went well.\N{\rCHT}好吧 一切順利{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.18,1:18:46.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,When I was a boy, growing up in Nigeria...\N{\rCHT}當我還是個孩子的時候 在奈及利亞長大…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.58,1:18:52.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,Heaven was here...\N{\rCHT}天堂在這裡…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.11,1:18:56.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,and America was here.\N{\rCHT}而美國就在這裡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.45,1:19:02.94,ENG,,0,0,0,,To me it was the place where God sent all of his favorite people.\N{\rCHT}對我來說天堂就是上帝把所有他喜歡的人召集在一起的地方{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.96,1:19:08.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,You could be anything, you could do anything.\N{\rCHT}你可以想任何事 你可以做任何事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:10.15,1:19:15.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Americans were the manifestation of what God wanted us all to be.\N{\rCHT}我以為上帝喜歡的大概就是美國人那樣的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.47,1:19:23.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,I have never wanted anything...\N{\rCHT}我從來沒有這麼想…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.60,1:19:28.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,as much as I wanted to be accepted as an American.\N{\rCHT}成為一個為人所接受的美國人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.65,1:19:39.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,But Mike Webster goes mad, and nobody asks why.\N{\rCHT}但是邁克·韋伯斯特瘋的時候竟然沒有人去問為什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.97,1:19:45.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,They make fun of him, they insult him on TV.\N{\rCHT}他們嘲笑他 在電視上侮辱他{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.49,1:19:48.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,And now they want to pretend that his disease does not exist.\N{\rCHT}而現在他們又想要假裝他的病是不存在的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:48.76,1:19:51.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,And they want to bury me.\N{\rCHT}他們還想掩蓋我的發現{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.33,1:19:57.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's offensive.\N{\rCHT}這是攻擊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:58.24,1:20:01.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am offended\N{\rCHT}我是靶子{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.65,1:20:08.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am the wrong person to have discovered this.\N{\rCHT}我不應該發現這個{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.58,1:20:17.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,There is no coincidence in this world.\N{\rCHT}這世界上沒有巧合{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.63,1:20:25.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell me, what is the statistical probability that you?\N{\rCHT}告訴我 你 不僅僅作為一個醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.11,1:20:30.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not just a doctor, but Bennet Omalu...\N{\rCHT}還是班尼特·奧奧馬魯 來到美國{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.80,1:20:34.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,came to America, ended up here,\N{\rCHT}紮根在這裡 在這個腐朽的地方{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.18,1:20:40.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,This rusty place, for you alone to be the one to see this?\N{\rCHT}你一個人看著這一切的概率是多大？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.10,1:20:50.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,When I arrived in New York...\N{\rCHT}當我抵達紐約的時候…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.41,1:20:55.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,- I was attacked. - What happened?\N{\rCHT}- 我遇到了襲擊 - 發生什麼事了？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.31,1:20:58.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Something that is better left unsaid.\N{\rCHT}還是不說比較好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.96,1:21:04.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,But that man, almost broke me.\N{\rCHT}但那個人 快要把我打死了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.47,1:21:10.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,I wanted to give up and go back.\N{\rCHT}我想要放棄了 想回去{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.89,1:21:16.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,But I knew God.\N{\rCHT}但是我相信上帝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.74,1:21:20.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,I decided to trust his wisdom.\N{\rCHT}我相信上帝的聖明{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.80,1:21:23.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I stayed.\N{\rCHT}我留下了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.38,1:21:31.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,And now I am looking at this man... An Omalu Onyemalukwubwe.\N{\rCHT}而現在我眼前的這個人… 奧瑪魯·杌隉瑪魯庫伯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.53,1:21:37.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,your name, it means "If you know...\N{\rCHT}你的名字 意味著"如果你知道…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.20,1:21:40.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,You must come forth and speak".\N{\rCHT}你必須站出來公之於眾"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.68,1:21:46.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,- How did you know that? - I called your father.\N{\rCHT}- 你是怎麼知道那個的？- 我打電話給你的父親了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:46.49,1:21:50.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,- He was pleased to hear from me. - Yes. I am sure he was.\N{\rCHT}- 他聽到我說的話很高興 - 我相信他很高興{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.89,1:21:55.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,If you don't speak for the dead, who will?\N{\rCHT}假如你不把死因說出來 誰來說？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.16,1:21:59.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,You are of the Igbo tribe, Bennet.\N{\rCHT}你是義博部落出生的人 班尼特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.73,1:22:02.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,When you have the truth, the thing\N{\rCHT}當你知道了事情的真相 有被告知{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.46,1:22:05.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,you are told you cannot do is the thing you must do.\N{\rCHT}你不能做的事 那就是你要做的事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.61,1:22:12.35,ENG,,0,0,0,,Embrace that, and nothing created by man can bring you down.\N{\rCHT}去吧 沒有人能夠打倒你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.86,1:22:22.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Omalu's gone to the press now, listen to this.\N{\rCHT}奧奧馬魯去出版社了 聽這個{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.34,1:22:27.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,"After examining the remains of former National Football League player Andre Waters,\N{\rCHT}在國家橄欖球運動員安德魯·瓦特斯的遺體解剖結束後{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.73,1:22:31.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,a neuropathologist in Pittsburgh, Dr.Bennet Omalu is claiming...\N{\rCHT}在匹茲堡的驗屍官班尼特·奧奧馬魯醫生聲稱…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.77,1:22:36.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,That Mr.Waters had sustained brain damage from playing football, and he says...\N{\rCHT}瓦特斯先生在職業生涯期間受到了持續的腦損傷…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.42,1:22:39.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,that led to his depression and ultimate death.\N{\rCHT}最終導致了他的抑鬱和死亡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.14,1:22:43.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,It gets worse.\N{\rCHT}越來越糟糕{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.15,1:22:47.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dr.Julian Bailes, Medical Director for the Centre for the Study of Retired Athletes,\N{\rCHT}朱利安·貝爾斯醫生 退役運動員研究中心主任{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:47.74,1:22:49.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,and the Chairman of the Department of Neurosurgery...\N{\rCHT}西維吉尼亞大學的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.82,1:22:51.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,of West Virginia University said:\N{\rCHT}神經外科學系的主席 表示：{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.81,1:22:54.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Unfortunately, I'm not shocked."\N{\rCHT}"很遺憾 我並不感到驚訝"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.27,1:22:58.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's more Omalu and more Bailes.\N{\rCHT}會有更多的奧瑪魯和貝爾斯出現的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.07,1:23:00.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bailes. Why do I know that name?\N{\rCHT}貝爾斯 這個名字怎麼有點耳熟？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.48,1:23:04.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Steeler's Team Doctor, Neurologist for the Players Association.\N{\rCHT}鋼人隊的團隊醫生 球員協會的神經學專家{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.91,1:23:09.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Wow... - Yeah, Wow.\N{\rCHT}- 哇… - 是的 哇{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:09.43,1:23:12.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,The Times is calling it a potential epidemic.\N{\rCHT}《紐約時報》稱這是潛在的瘟疫{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.47,1:23:18.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Paul... It's not the sports section, not science.\N{\rCHT}保羅… 這不是什麼體育專欄 不是科學期刊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.70,1:23:23.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's A1, front page, New York Times.\N{\rCHT}在紐約時報的首頁 頭條{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.35,1:23:30.00,ENG,,0,0,0,,Apparently, the commissioner has been yearning for years...\N{\rCHT}顯然 總裁多年來一直渴望…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:30.05,1:23:34.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,to go back to his litigator... since Paul Tagliabue announced that he would retire...\N{\rCHT}根據律師的回饋… 保羅·塔利亞布埃宣佈他將退役…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.66,1:23:37.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,in July, after nearly 17 years...\N{\rCHT}在七月 差不多17年後…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.92,1:23:43.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Prized, The most lucrative and stabilizing reign, perhaps in the history.\N{\rCHT}國家橄欖球聯盟 也許是史上最有價值最穩定最賺錢的體育聯盟{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.24,1:23:45.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Football at the NFL owners meeting in O'Doherty...\N{\rCHT}在奧多爾蒂國家橄欖球聯盟俱樂部經理會議上…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.65,1:23:49.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,There's a new sheriff in town. His name is Roger Goodell.\N{\rCHT}一個新總裁出現了 他的名字叫羅傑·古德爾{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.87,1:23:54.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,What I'm here to do now is protect the shield.\N{\rCHT}現在讓我來為這個聯盟說句話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.70,1:23:57.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,The NFL isn't just a sports league.\N{\rCHT}國家橄欖球聯盟不僅僅是一個體育聯賽{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.74,1:24:00.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's an entertainment product.\N{\rCHT}它也是一個娛樂產品{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.26,1:24:02.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,America's Game.\N{\rCHT}是美國人的遊戲{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.27,1:24:04.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,I want us to go on enjoying...\N{\rCHT}我希望我們能繼續享受它給我們帶來的樂趣…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.38,1:24:06.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Allegheny County Coroner...\N{\rCHT}阿勒格尼縣驗屍中心…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.23,1:24:07.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Sure, one second.\N{\rCHT}好的 稍等{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.53,1:24:10.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's Dr.Julian Bailes.\N{\rCHT}朱利安·貝爾斯醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.40,1:24:12.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yes, yeah. - Here he is.\N{\rCHT}- 好的 - 他來了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.30,1:24:16.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Julian - Hey, Turn on the TV.\N{\rCHT}- 朱利安 - 嗯 打開電視機{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.99,1:24:18.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm watching.\N{\rCHT}嗯 我在看了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.10,1:24:21.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,You asked for a face to face with the Commissioner... Man to Man?\N{\rCHT}你想要的和委員面對面的？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.89,1:24:26.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Goodell and the NFL are asking for a concussion summit.\N{\rCHT}古德爾邀請你出席國家橄欖球聯賽的腦震盪研究會議{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.21,1:24:30.29,ENG,,0,0,0,,A full presentation in Chicago next week.\N{\rCHT}下周在芝加哥進行一個完整的演示{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.02,1:24:34.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,They heard you, you have your shot.\N{\rCHT}他們知道你了 該你出手了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.17,1:24:39.01,ENG,,0,0,0,,Julian...\N{\rCHT}朱利安…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.84,1:24:54.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why don't you throw in some football stuff?\N{\rCHT}你為什麼不加入一些有關橄欖球的材料？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.77,1:24:58.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,Some non-medical terms, things we'd say.\N{\rCHT}我們需要說的東西 一些非醫學術語{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.49,1:25:01.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,Why do I need to say things they'd say?\N{\rCHT}我們為什麼要說他們要說的是東西？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.94,1:25:05.58,ENG,,0,0,0,,I thought I was here for the other reason.\N{\rCHT}我還以為以為我在這裡是為了別的原因{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.80,1:25:11.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,You have what? 7 or 8 degrees? you're one of the smartest people they'll ever meet...\N{\rCHT}你有什麼？7個甚至8個學歷？你將是他們見過的最聰明的人之一{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.25,1:25:18.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know what? You're gonna be fine...\N{\rCHT}你知道嗎？你會成功的…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.77,1:25:30.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,How about you?\N{\rCHT}你沒事吧？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.07,1:25:33.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,How will you be?\N{\rCHT}你會怎麼樣？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.12,1:25:41.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know, it is a mindless, violent game.\N{\rCHT}你知道 這是一個愚蠢又暴力的遊戲{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.14,1:25:43.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,And then it's Shakespeare.\N{\rCHT}很莎士比亞{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.91,1:25:45.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,I mean to me, it's like life that way.\N{\rCHT}我的意思是對我而言 就像生活一樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.99,1:25:48.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I know you can't see how...\N{\rCHT}我知道你不明白…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.12,1:25:53.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,exciting, and beautiful all that is, and I don't blame you.\N{\rCHT}那是多麼的刺激多麼的競猜 我不會怪你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.87,1:26:00.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,But what I'm trying to tell you is... This is not fun for me.\N{\rCHT}但我要告訴你的是… 這對我來說一點也不好玩{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.82,1:26:05.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,All of the people we're gonna see tomorrow, I know them personally.\N{\rCHT}明天我們看到的所有人 私底下我都認識{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.55,1:26:09.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,And that feeling you have when someone you love and admire,\N{\rCHT}你對於那些你喜歡和尊敬的人讓你滾蛋{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.53,1:26:11.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,screws you over...\N{\rCHT}所產生的一切感覺…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.51,1:26:17.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're gonna have that feeling...\N{\rCHT}他們會有的就是那種感覺…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.31,1:26:21.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because of me.\N{\rCHT}因為我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.30,1:26:25.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,And there's not a damn thing I can do about it.\N{\rCHT}我卻什麼都做不到{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:45.81,1:26:48.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Hey - We have to talk.\N{\rCHT}- 嘿 - 我們必須談談{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.34,1:26:49.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?\N{\rCHT}怎麼了？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.39,1:26:55.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,There is no easy way to say this, so I'm just going to say it.\N{\rCHT}沒法委婉地說 我就直說了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.16,1:26:58.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're not going to let you speak.\N{\rCHT}他們不想讓你說話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.38,1:27:00.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,What?\N{\rCHT}什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.28,1:27:04.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,They don't even want you in the room.\N{\rCHT}他們甚至不希望你在會場{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.24,1:27:08.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,They want me to do it.\N{\rCHT}他們想讓我去做{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.31,1:27:12.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,- One of their own. - One of their own.\N{\rCHT}- 一個他們自己的人 - 一個他們自己的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.85,1:27:15.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,- So they want to pretend... - that you don't even exist, that's right...\N{\rCHT}- 所以他們想假裝… - 假裝你不存在 是的…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.72,1:27:20.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,- They still have to sit and listen. - To you\N{\rCHT}- 他們還得坐下來聽 - 你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.21,1:27:24.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yes, you blew up their whole world. - And yours, Julian.\N{\rCHT}- 是的 你毀了他們的世界 - 還有你的 朱利安{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.35,1:27:26.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, mine.\N{\rCHT}是的 還有我的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:26.56,1:27:32.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because how can it be possible, that some African Voodoo Doctor\N{\rCHT}因為覺得一個非洲巫術醫生怎麼可能{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.44,1:27:36.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,could understand this subject better than them.\N{\rCHT}會比他們更深入地瞭解這個問題{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.46,1:27:38.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,Or even better than you\N{\rCHT}甚至比你還瞭解{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.01,1:27:42.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wait a second, you think this is about Bennet Omalu?\N{\rCHT}等一會兒 你覺得這是針對班尼特·奧奧馬魯嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:42.87,1:27:45.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not here because of you, I'm here because people are dying.\N{\rCHT}我會在這裡不是因為你 而是因為有人在死去{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.96,1:27:51.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,You are here for redemption. You are here to use me to cleanse your sins.\N{\rCHT}你在這裡是為了贖罪 你在這裡是想用我去洗刷你的罪惡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.80,1:27:55.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,You self-righteous bastard.\N{\rCHT}你這個自以為是的混蛋{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.99,1:27:59.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea what I could have? How much I could have?\N{\rCHT}你知道如果站到聯盟那邊一直守口如瓶{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.01,1:28:04.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,If I went back to my side of the ball and just kept my mouth shut.\N{\rCHT}我能得到什麼嗎？知道我能得到多少嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.13,1:28:09.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Everything in my world is telling me not to agree with you,\N{\rCHT}我世界中的一切事物都在阻止我同意你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.21,1:28:10.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,except one.\N{\rCHT}只有一個例外{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.03,1:28:13.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,Science.\N{\rCHT}科學{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.47,1:28:15.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,So, here I am.\N{\rCHT}這才是我在這兒的理由{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.73,1:28:19.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Up here beside you, not down there in that audience with them.\N{\rCHT}站在你旁邊 而不是和他們坐在觀眾席{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.90,1:28:25.71,ENG,,0,0,0,,What more can I do to prove myself to you?\N{\rCHT}還需要我做什麼向你證明嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.53,1:28:57.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am sorry.\N{\rCHT}我很抱歉{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.25,1:29:01.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,Convince them, Julian.\N{\rCHT}說服他們 朱利安{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.33,1:29:19.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know, my father can't remember a god damn thing\N{\rCHT}我父親記不住這該死的事{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.00,1:29:22.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,He never played a day of football.\N{\rCHT}他從沒打過一天橄欖球{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.16,1:29:25.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,He was too busy working in a factory, you quack.\N{\rCHT}他忙著在工廠工作 你這個庸醫{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.29,1:29:26.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,I beg your pardon?\N{\rCHT}再說一遍？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.64,1:29:29.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,You take your bullshit science and go back to Africa.\N{\rCHT}帶著你的狗屎科學滾回非洲去吧{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.90,1:29:32.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,And get away from our game.\N{\rCHT}離我們的遊戲遠點{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.69,1:29:36.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,What happened?\N{\rCHT}怎麼了？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.71,1:29:39.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Roger Goodell just said that Justin Strzelczyk\N{\rCHT}羅傑·古德爾只是說了賈斯汀·斯托克斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.51,1:29:41.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,May have got his concussion swimming.\N{\rCHT}可能是游泳時候造成的腦震盪{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.59,1:29:45.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,- In a swimming pool. - That, That's insanity.\N{\rCHT}- 在一個游泳池 - 完全是胡說{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.88,1:29:47.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,This whole thing was staged.\N{\rCHT}先不說這個{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:47.93,1:29:51.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,They needed to say they heard us so they could god damn bury us.\N{\rCHT}他們需要說他們聽了我們的了 那麼他們才能埋沒我們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.21,1:29:53.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,The science means nothing to them.\N{\rCHT}科學對他們來說毫無意義{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.64,1:29:56.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is an important day, in the National Football League...\N{\rCHT}對國家橄欖球聯盟來說今天是個重要的日子…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.82,1:29:59.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,We've had some very good dialogue,\N{\rCHT}我們收到了很多重要的意見{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.29,1:30:02.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,Which will help us improve the care for our players.\N{\rCHT}這將幫助我們進一步照顧我們的球員{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.91,1:30:08.12,ENG,,0,0,0,,What do you think when you hear about former NFL players suffering from symptoms that\N{\rCHT}當你聽到很多退役球員患有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.17,1:30:11.36,ENG,,0,0,0,,has only been seen in boxers and people that are over 80 years old?\N{\rCHT}只有拳擊手和80歲以上的人才有的病症時怎麼想？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.42,1:30:14.83,ENG,,0,0,0,,I mean what does that say about the effects of concussions on players?\N{\rCHT}我的意思是說腦震盪對球員的影響有什麼想說的？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.87,1:30:19.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm not a doctor here, but you have to look at their entire medical history.\N{\rCHT}我不是醫生 但是你看看整個醫學發展史{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.63,1:30:22.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is an evolving science, and that's okay.\N{\rCHT}這是一項不斷發展的科學 就是這樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.81,1:30:29.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,While I agree with the commissioner, no empirically determined proof was presented today,\N{\rCHT}我同意委員的看法 今天並沒有提出關鍵性的證據{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.17,1:30:32.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,because there simply isn't any.\N{\rCHT}因為根本就沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:33.25,1:30:36.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,Because according to the NFL's own numbers\N{\rCHT}因為根據國家橄欖球聯盟的資料統計{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.25,1:30:40.59,ENG,,0,0,0,,half of all players with concussions are sent back into the same game.\N{\rCHT}超過一半的得過腦震盪的球員最後都回到比賽中去了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.63,1:30:44.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Including some who were actually knocked out cold.\N{\rCHT}包括一些曾被撞暈過的人{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.18,1:30:49.06,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ira Casson, was head of a team of NFL doctors\N{\rCHT}艾勒·卡森 曾是國際橄欖球聯盟的團隊主管醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.13,1:30:50.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,who had looked into the issue,\N{\rCHT}他看到這個問題以後{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.79,1:30:55.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,and determined that the concern over head injuries was overblown.\N{\rCHT}認為頭部受傷的擔憂顯然被誇大了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.07,1:30:57.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is there any evidence, as far as you're concerned...\N{\rCHT}從您的觀點來說 有沒有什麼和…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.08,1:31:00.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,that links multiple head injuries\N{\rCHT}出現在職業橄欖球運動員裡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.28,1:31:03.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,among pro football players with... depression?\N{\rCHT}多人顱腦損傷… 抑鬱症相關聯的證據？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:03.29,1:31:04.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,No.\N{\rCHT}沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.38,1:31:07.14,ENG,,0,0,0,,- With Dementia? - No.\N{\rCHT}- 老年癡呆？- 沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.34,1:31:10.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,- With early onset of Alzheimer's? - No.\N{\rCHT}- 伴隨早期老年癡呆症發作？- 沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.92,1:31:14.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Is there any evidence as of today that links\N{\rCHT}沒有任何證據可以證明{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:14.36,1:31:18.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,Multiple head injuries with any long term problem like that?\N{\rCHT}多次頭部損傷會產生後遺症的問題？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:18.94,1:31:20.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,- In NFL players? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 在國家橄欖球聯盟球員中嗎？- 是的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.23,1:31:21.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,No.\N{\rCHT}沒有{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.64,1:31:50.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hey little one.\N{\rCHT}嘿 小傢伙{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.26,1:31:54.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is your father.\N{\rCHT}我是你老爸{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.99,1:32:01.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am in deep shit.\N{\rCHT}我踩到狗屎了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.68,1:32:07.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,I have not done anything wrong...\N{\rCHT}雖然我並沒有做錯什麼…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:09.20,1:32:12.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,but I am being punished.\N{\rCHT}但是我被懲罰了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.94,1:32:22.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,It might not be so nice, when you get out here\N{\rCHT}當你離開媽媽肚子的時候可能發現世界並不美好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.93,1:32:29.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,You are still with God.\N{\rCHT}你現在和上帝在一起{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.44,1:32:34.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,Please ask him to help me.\N{\rCHT}請讓他幫幫我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.87,1:33:07.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's alright, it's okay...\N{\rCHT}都過去了 沒關係…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.83,1:33:16.86,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What is this? - This is the FBI.\N{\rCHT}- 什麼情況？- 他們來自FBI{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.90,1:33:19.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Apparently I'm being relieved of my duties.\N{\rCHT}顯然我被解除責任了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.92,1:33:21.44,ENG,,0,0,0,,What? I don't understand.\N{\rCHT}什麼？我不明白{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.49,1:33:25.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dr.Wecht has been indicted on 84 federal counts including...\N{\rCHT}威切特醫生被聯邦方面指控從1984年開始…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.24,1:33:28.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,Please Tex, let me at least have the joy of telling him.\N{\rCHT}拜託 特克斯 至少讓我有告訴他這多麼有趣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.80,1:33:32.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm being indicted on 84 federal counts,\N{\rCHT}我被聯邦法院指控從84年開始{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.42,1:33:36.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,including mail fraud, wire fraud, other related offences.\N{\rCHT}進行郵件欺詐、通信欺詐、等相關罪行{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:36.56,1:33:42.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,Arising out of my use of government resources, to advance my private practice.\N{\rCHT}利用政府資源扶持我的私人診所{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.54,1:33:44.51,ENG,,0,0,0,,Including but not limited to:\N{\rCHT}包括但不限於:{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:44.57,1:33:49.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mileage vouchers, misuse of office stationary,\N{\rCHT}濫用交通補助和辦公用品{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.46,1:33:53.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,and my personal use of the fax machine.\N{\rCHT}還有違規使用傳真機{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.66,1:33:55.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Faxes? - Yeah.\N{\rCHT}- 傳真？- 是的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.93,1:33:58.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,They could not have come up with something this stupid in Nigeria.\N{\rCHT}這些愚蠢的理由在奈及利亞都行不通{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.93,1:34:02.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,This man has been a public servant for decades.\N{\rCHT}這個人幾十年來一直為人民服務{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.62,1:34:05.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cyril.\N{\rCHT}西瑞爾{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.31,1:34:09.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,Have you ever performed any private services on county time?\N{\rCHT}你有沒有做過任何以公謀私的事情？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.03,1:34:11.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Have I?\N{\rCHT}我？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.08,1:34:15.16,ENG,,0,0,0,,Apparently we've both hurt the government's feelings\N{\rCHT}顯然我們都傷害了政府的的感情{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.23,1:34:20.27,ENG,,0,0,0,,Are you referring to the death row case? Where I used my personal time.\N{\rCHT}你指的是死刑案件嗎？我都是用的業餘時間{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.31,1:34:23.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,We don't want you, Dr.Omalu. But we can have you.\N{\rCHT}我們不會為難你 奧瑪魯醫生 但是我們需要你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.80,1:34:27.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,- And what does that mean? - That means they want your testimony.\N{\rCHT}- 這是什麼意思？- 意思是說他們需要你的證詞{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.82,1:34:32.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Against you? - Yes.\N{\rCHT}- 針對你？- 是的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:32.98,1:34:35.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,I understand.\N{\rCHT}我明白了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.37,1:34:39.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,You are attacking him, to get to me.\N{\rCHT}你們先攻擊他 然後就是我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.90,1:34:41.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,I know.\N{\rCHT}我懂了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.69,1:34:45.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is because his name is on my research.\N{\rCHT}這是因為他的名字在我的調查報告上{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.55,1:34:47.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,What research is that?\N{\rCHT}什麼調查？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.06,1:34:50.60,ENG,,0,0,0,,I will resign first.\N{\rCHT}我會儘快辭職的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.63,1:34:53.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,In which case your immigration status will be revised.\N{\rCHT}在這種情況下 你的移民身份將會發生變化{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.86,1:34:56.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,Since your status requires full-time employment.\N{\rCHT}因為你的身份需要全職工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:57.12,1:35:00.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Then I will get another job in another city.\N{\rCHT}我會去別的城市再找一份工作的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.52,1:35:03.40,ENG,,0,0,0,,- That would be fine.\N{\rCHT}那樣最好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.60,1:35:14.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bennet...\N{\rCHT}班尼特…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.36,1:35:30.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,All I asked, is that if you did this, we both came out okay.\N{\rCHT}我跟你說過 如果你要做 確保我們都能夠沒有麻煩{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.42,1:35:33.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Not professional ruination.\N{\rCHT}而不是丟了工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.17,1:35:39.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,Whoever... Whatever takes over from me...\N{\rCHT}任何人… 不管誰取代我…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.45,1:35:45.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,They're gonna want the CTE information, you know that.\N{\rCHT}他們都是為了腦損傷的資料{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.77,1:35:51.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,- What if they show up here with a warrant? - On suspicion of what? Science?\N{\rCHT}- 如果他們帶著正當理由出現在這裡呢？- 懷疑什麼？科學？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:51.05,1:35:54.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Ah, on suspicion of bullshit. We got screwed...\N{\rCHT}啊 因涉嫌胡說 我們受到了不公正的待遇…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.93,1:35:57.30,ENG,,0,0,0,,You didn't deserve it.\N{\rCHT}這不是你該得到的結果{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.78,1:36:00.89,ENG,,0,0,0,,You know the worst part? How easy it was.\N{\rCHT}你知道最糟糕的是什麼嗎？太容易了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.93,1:36:03.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cyril, they are not going to make me say...\N{\rCHT}西瑞爾 他們休想讓我說出{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.76,1:36:05.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,one word against you.\N{\rCHT}一個指控你的字{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.52,1:36:07.74,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you gonna say?\N{\rCHT}你會說什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.55,1:36:11.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,"Cyril Wecht's a loud-mouthed asshole"?\N{\rCHT}"西瑞爾·威切特是個白癡"？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.06,1:36:15.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't care, I'm tired.\N{\rCHT}我不在乎 我累了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.06,1:36:17.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,My balls are low.\N{\rCHT}我年紀大了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.02,1:36:27.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,I didn't do good enough by you.\N{\rCHT}我沒有為做好什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.99,1:36:35.21,ENG,,0,0,0,,Cyril... I can not go back to Nigeria.\N{\rCHT}西瑞爾… 我不能回到奈及利亞{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.18,1:36:40.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,Everything that I am is here.\N{\rCHT}我的一切都在這兒{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.71,1:36:45.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,My child has got to be born in America.\N{\rCHT}我的孩子要出生在美國{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.19,1:36:51.23,ENG,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I'll get you a job.\N{\rCHT}別擔心 我會給你一份工作{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.26,1:36:54.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,You can work with me in the prison laundry.\N{\rCHT}你可以和我在監獄的洗衣房一起幹活{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.80,1:37:04.70,ENG,,0,0,0,,Call the surgeon. We need a god damned drink.\N{\rCHT}打電話外科醫生 我們需要喝幾杯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:01.88,1:38:03.57,ENG,,0,0,0,,I solved the problem.\N{\rCHT}我把這個問題解決了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:03.61,1:38:06.48,ENG,,0,0,0,,All the have to do is put on the side of the helmet,\N{\rCHT}所有要做的就是把安全帽放到一邊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.62,1:38:11.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,"The Surgeon General has determined that playing football is hazardous to your health."\N{\rCHT}"普通外科醫生就會認定打球對你的健康是有害的"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:11.19,1:38:13.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,You gotta put it on both sides of the helmet.\N{\rCHT}你必須把雙方的安全帽都拿掉{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.16,1:38:30.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,Did you know that Paul Tagliabue, this is the former commissioner Tagliabue...\N{\rCHT}你知不知道保羅·塔利亞布埃 聯盟前委員…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.43,1:38:33.52,ENG,,0,0,0,,Did you know that Paul was a partner at Covington & Burling?\N{\rCHT}你知道科文頓柏靈律師事務所的合夥人保羅嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.56,1:38:37.04,ENG,,0,0,0,,which is the same law firm that represented the Big 7 Tobacco companies.\N{\rCHT}也就是7大煙草公司的事務所{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:37.13,1:38:39.99,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Course he was. - And now they're representing the National Football League.\N{\rCHT}- 當然 - 現在他們代言了國家橄欖球聯盟{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.99,1:38:42.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,Of course they do.\N{\rCHT}他們當然會這樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.58,1:38:53.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,In my last year with the Steelers,\N{\rCHT}我在鋼人隊的最後一年{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.20,1:38:56.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,We moved a game from a Sunday to a Tuesday because of a blizzard.\N{\rCHT}因為暴風雪 我們把比賽從周日改到了週二{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.94,1:38:59.93,ENG,,0,0,0,,And the league said that they weren't concerned about the ratings,\N{\rCHT}聯盟說不用擔心收視率{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.94,1:39:03.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,because the league was immune from acts of God.\N{\rCHT}因為聯盟是被神保佑的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.29,1:39:28.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bennet! Bennet!\N{\rCHT}班尼特 班尼特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.50,1:39:58.03,ENG,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry, there's no heartbeat.\N{\rCHT}很抱歉 沒有心跳了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.81,1:40:03.61,ENG,,0,0,0,,May, May we have the room?\N{\rCHT}能讓我們兩個人一起呆一會兒嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.87,1:40:07.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,Please, Excuse us, thank you.\N{\rCHT}拜託了 謝謝{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:24.80,1:40:26.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am so sorry.\N{\rCHT}我很抱歉{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.04,1:40:30.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,I am sorry that our baby's dead.\N{\rCHT}孩子沒了我很抱歉{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.80,1:40:33.11,ENG,,0,0,0,,This is my fault.\N{\rCHT}都是我的錯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.45,1:41:07.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,I wish I'd never met Mike Webster.\N{\rCHT}真希望我從沒見過邁克·韋伯斯特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.00,1:41:14.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,They destroyed us.\N{\rCHT}他們毀了我們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.82,1:41:22.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I don't understand why it is happening this way.\N{\rCHT}我不明白事情為什麼會這樣{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:26.08,1:41:28.92,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bennet, listen to me.\N{\rCHT}班尼特 聽我說{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:30.87,1:41:34.97,ENG,,0,0,0,,Do you know what I chose to fake?\N{\rCHT}你知道我選擇的明燈是誰嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:39.07,1:41:41.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,You.\N{\rCHT}是你{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:47.26,1:41:53.66,ENG,,0,0,0,,- We will have this family. - Yes, we will.\N{\rCHT}- 我們會有個家的 - 嗯 我們會有的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.12,1:41:58.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,Just not here.\N{\rCHT}但不是在這兒{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.53,1:42:04.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,We have to go.\N{\rCHT}我們得走了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:39.28,1:42:42.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hello, Mr Omalu?\N{\rCHT}你好 奧瑪魯先生？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.82,1:42:46.39,ENG,,0,0,0,,Doctor Omalu.\N{\rCHT}奧瑪魯醫生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:46.41,1:42:49.37,ENG,,0,0,0,,I just need the measurements for the flat screens.\N{\rCHT}我們需要知道你的電視機尺寸{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.37,1:42:53.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,That won't be necessary.\N{\rCHT}沒必要了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.68,1:44:39.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,{\c&He0e0e0&\fs20}加利福利亞 洛帝
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.18,1:44:39.92,CHT,,0,0,0,,{\c&He0e0e0&\fs20}三年後
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.53,1:45:32.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell me what happened to you, Jose.\N{\rCHT}告訴我你怎麼了 約瑟{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.21,1:45:35.24,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell me.\N{\rCHT}告訴我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.88,1:45:38.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,It's going to be okay.\N{\rCHT}都會好的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.01,1:45:51.76,ENG,,0,0,0,,My mind keeps slipping.\N{\rCHT}我的思維一直在弱化{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:51.80,1:45:55.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,I can't seem to find the damn words no more.\N{\rCHT}我甚至不回說話了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.54,1:45:57.95,ENG,,0,0,0,,What?\N{\rCHT}什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:01.31,1:46:03.19,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yeah Yeah Yeah.\N{\rCHT}嗯 嗯 嗯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.42,1:46:09.55,ENG,,0,0,0,,I just can't do this, I'm sorry.\N{\rCHT}我不行了 我很抱歉{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.07,1:46:55.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Yes? - Bennet it's Julian.\N{\rCHT}- 誰啊？- 是我朱利安{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.65,1:47:00.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dave Duerson killed himself today.\N{\rCHT}戴夫·杜爾森今天自殺了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:00.93,1:47:03.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,He shot himself in the chest, in the heart.\N{\rCHT}他朝自己的胸部開了一槍{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:03.82,1:47:05.87,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hold on, Hold on.\N{\rCHT}等等 等等{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:11.57,1:47:14.32,ENG,,0,0,0,,- Oh My God. - He left a note.\N{\rCHT}- 我的天 - 他留下了一張字條{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:14.35,1:47:18.43,ENG,,0,0,0,,He wants his brain to be donated, to be examined.\N{\rCHT}他希望死後將大腦捐贈出去做研究{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:22.01,1:47:24.50,ENG,,0,0,0,,They said that we were right.\N{\rCHT}他認為我們是正確的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.24,1:47:30.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,Bennet, are you there?\N{\rCHT}班尼特 你在嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:31.40,1:47:33.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,Yes, Yes, I'm here.\N{\rCHT}嗯 我在{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.63,1:47:40.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,A Pro-Bowler in that deep with NFL leadership, killing himself in the way he killed himself.\N{\rCHT}一個國家橄欖球聯盟專業的頂級的投球手 用自己的方式自殺了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.01,1:47:43.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,They can't explain this one away.\N{\rCHT}他們解釋不了這個{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:44.22,1:47:46.82,ENG,,0,0,0,,Players are gonna want to hear from you now.\N{\rCHT}球員們現在想要聽見你的聲音{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:54.05,1:47:56.54,ENG,,0,0,0,,Trying to find the...\N{\rCHT}我想找那件…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:14.17,1:48:16.80,ENG,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to say to them.\N{\rCHT}我不知道該對他們說什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.05,1:48:24.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,Tell them what's really happening.\N{\rCHT}告訴他們到底發生了什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:13.54,1:49:14.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,Hello.\N{\rCHT}大家好{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:20.00,1:49:24.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,A small boy came to me...\N{\rCHT}一個小男孩來找我…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:25.59,1:49:29.10,ENG,,0,0,0,,and said, Mister, why do you hate football?\N{\rCHT}說:先生 為什麼你那麼討厭橄欖球？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:29.36,1:49:31.56,ENG,,0,0,0,,I said I don't hate football.\N{\rCHT}我說我不討厭橄欖球啊{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:32.24,1:49:35.34,ENG,,0,0,0,,He said: "Yes, my father said you hate football."\N{\rCHT}他說："我爸爸說你討厭橄欖球"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.08,1:49:38.96,ENG,,0,0,0,,I said, "You tell your father to come see me."\N{\rCHT}我說"你告訴你父親來見我"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.28,1:49:46.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,My wife watches the games.\N{\rCHT}我的妻子喜歡在看比賽{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:46.57,1:49:51.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,And she will scream and she will jump.\N{\rCHT}她會尖叫 甚至會跳起來{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:51.18,1:49:53.65,ENG,,0,0,0,,She startles me, a lot.\N{\rCHT}她總是嚇到我{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.82,1:50:03.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,But through her eyes I can see the beauty, and the grace...\N{\rCHT}但通過她的眼睛 我能看到美 看到優雅…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.31,1:50:05.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,The power.\N{\rCHT}還有能量{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.03,1:50:11.78,ENG,,0,0,0,,I said to her that I wished I'd never met Mike Webster.\N{\rCHT}我告訴她 我寧願從沒見過邁克·韋伯斯特{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.36,1:50:26.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,But that was before I knew him.\N{\rCHT}但在我認識他之前{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.43,1:50:35.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,He has given me a great gift.\N{\rCHT}他給了我一個大禮物{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:36.97,1:50:39.98,ENG,,0,0,0,,A dangerous gift.\N{\rCHT}這禮物是危險的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.95,1:50:43.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,The gift of knowing.\N{\rCHT}這禮物是知識{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:45.63,1:50:50.31,ENG,,0,0,0,,When a man is a soldier, he knows what is at risk.\N{\rCHT}一個士兵 知道什麼是危險{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.34,1:50:53.72,ENG,,0,0,0,,He may be injured or even killed.\N{\rCHT}可能會受傷 甚至死亡{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:55.57,1:50:58.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,But when a man is a football player,\N{\rCHT}但是作為一個職業球員{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:59.41,1:51:03.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,He knows he may break his arm, or his leg\N{\rCHT}知道自己可能會斷手 斷腿{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:03.82,1:51:09.15,ENG,,0,0,0,,He does not know that he can lose his mind.\N{\rCHT}他不知道還會失去自己的思想{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:10.01,1:51:13.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,His family, his money.\N{\rCHT}失去家庭和金錢{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.00,1:51:17.33,ENG,,0,0,0,,His life.\N{\rCHT}還有他的生活{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:19.02,1:51:21.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,They have to know.\N{\rCHT}他們應該知道{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:26.74,1:51:31.49,ENG,,0,0,0,,Mike Webster, Justin Strzelczyk\N{\rCHT}邁克·韋伯斯特 賈斯汀·斯托克斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:31.53,1:51:36.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,Terry Long, Andre Waters,\N{\rCHT}特裡·隆 安德魯·瓦特斯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.84,1:51:39.20,ENG,,0,0,0,,Dave Duerson.\N{\rCHT}戴夫·杜爾森{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:40.43,1:51:43.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,By Dying...\N{\rCHT}他們通過死亡…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:43.25,1:51:45.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,They speak for the living.\N{\rCHT}來為生存代言{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.04,1:51:49.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,And I speak for them.\N{\rCHT}而我為他們代言{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:51.02,1:51:53.77,ENG,,0,0,0,,That is all I do.\N{\rCHT}這就是我所做的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.98,1:51:58.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Forgive them.\N{\rCHT}原諒他們{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:01.41,1:52:04.02,ENG,,0,0,0,,Forgive Yourselves.\N{\rCHT}原諒自己{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:09.96,1:52:12.46,ENG,,0,0,0,,Be at peace.\N{\rCHT}淡然處之{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:17.38,1:52:21.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,Commissioner Goodell, is there a link between\N{\rCHT}古德爾總裁 你認為打職業橄欖球{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:21.71,1:52:24.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,playing professional football and the likelihood\N{\rCHT}和腦相關的損傷之間{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:24.89,1:52:28.41,ENG,,0,0,0,,of contracting a brain related injury,\N{\rCHT}有沒有什麼關聯{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:28.49,1:52:34.18,ENG,,0,0,0,,Such as dementia, Alzheimer's, depression, or CTE?\N{\rCHT}如癡呆 阿爾茨海默氏症 抑鬱症 或慢性腦損傷病變？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:34.42,1:52:37.69,ENG,,0,0,0,,We are doing everything we possibly can for our players.\N{\rCHT}我們做了一切能為球員做的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:37.76,1:52:41.09,ENG,,0,0,0,,I just asked you a simple question. What's the answer?\N{\rCHT}我只想問你一個簡單的問題 答案是什麼？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:41.13,1:52:44.85,ENG,,0,0,0,,It sort of reminds me of the tobacco companies,\N{\rCHT}它讓我想起了煙草公司{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.88,1:52:47.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,Pre 90's, when they kept saying:\N{\rCHT}90年代以前 當他們不停地說:{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.11,1:52:52.75,ENG,,0,0,0,,"No, there is no link between smoking and damage to your health, or ill health effects."\N{\rCHT}"不 吸煙和健康問題 疾病因素沒有關聯性"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:52.78,1:52:59.45,ENG,,0,0,0,,And they were forced to admit that that was incorrect through a spate of litigation in the 1990's..\N{\rCHT}通過在1990年代一連串的訴訟 最終他們被迫承認那是不對的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.49,1:53:01.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,And my question to you is...\N{\rCHT}我要問你的是…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:02.16,1:53:05.47,ENG,,0,0,0,,We have heard from the NFL time and time again.\N{\rCHT}我們一次又一次的從國家橄欖球聯盟聽到{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:05.54,1:53:08.68,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're always studying, you're always trying.\N{\rCHT}你一直努力 你一直嘗試{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:08.76,1:53:10.91,ENG,,0,0,0,,- You're hopeful... I wanna know, - Son of a bitch\N{\rCHT}- 你很有前途… 我想知道 - 雜種{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:10.95,1:53:14.84,ENG,,0,0,0,,What are you doing in the negotiations that are going on now\N{\rCHT}你在這次洽談裡都做了什麼{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:14.88,1:53:18.17,ENG,,0,0,0,,to deal with this problem and other problems related\N{\rCHT}來處理這個問題和其他關於橄欖球運動員所{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:18.24,1:53:22.26,ENG,,0,0,0,,to the injuries that football players obtain,\N{\rCHT}受到傷害的問題{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:22.30,1:53:26.13,ENG,,0,0,0,,and it's impact on their health?\N{\rCHT}以及這些問題對他們健康的影響？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:26.16,1:53:27.67,ENG,,0,0,0,,You did all this.\N{\rCHT}你做的一切{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:27.72,1:53:29.90,ENG,,0,0,0,,I know my time is drawing to a close,\N{\rCHT}我知道時間不多了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:30.10,1:53:32.38,ENG,,0,0,0,,but let me just say this to Mr.Goodell\N{\rCHT}但是讓我告訴古德爾先生{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:32.61,1:53:40.22,ENG,,0,0,0,,and everybody who is here today, that I think that it's time Congress...\N{\rCHT}以及今天在場的每一個人 我認為國會是時候…{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:42.58,1:53:45.25,ENG,,0,0,0,,- First time in Washington? - Ah, yes.\N{\rCHT}- 第一次來華盛頓嗎？- 啊 是的{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.51,1:53:48.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Well, we're thrilled you accepted our invitation.\N{\rCHT}我們非常高興你能接受我們的邀請{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:48.08,1:53:51.81,ENG,,0,0,0,,I was very curious.\N{\rCHT}我很好奇{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:52.22,1:53:55.28,ENG,,0,0,0,,Chief Medical Examiner for Washington, DC\N{\rCHT}成為華盛頓特區首席法醫的話{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:55.32,1:53:58.53,ENG,,0,0,0,,means you would also consult with the CIA and FBI,\N{\rCHT}意味著你也得接受中央情報局和聯邦調查局的諮詢{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:53:58.76,1:54:01.07,ENG,,0,0,0,,and any foreign government requesting the assistance\N{\rCHT}還有任何外國政府對於{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.07,1:54:02.73,ENG,,0,0,0,,of the United States Government.\N{\rCHT}美國政府的援助請求{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:03.63,1:54:06.88,ENG,,0,0,0,,Essentially, you are America's forensic pathologist.\N{\rCHT}從本質上講 作為一名國家法醫病理學家{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.92,1:54:10.64,ENG,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't have to put on scrubs, perform an autopsy.\N{\rCHT}不需要像個實習醫生那樣進行屍檢{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:11.32,1:54:13.79,ENG,,0,0,0,,You're beyond all that now.\N{\rCHT}那些都不需要做了{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:18.97,1:54:21.05,ENG,,0,0,0,,Would you like to hear about the benefits package?\N{\rCHT}你想瞭解更多的相關福利嗎？{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:54:21.17,1:54:25.62,ENG,,0,0,0,,No, I mean, I'm sure it's fine.\N{\rCHT}不用了 我的意思是 肯定很好{\r}
